WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Alhamdulillah, Rabbul Alamin

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Ar-Rahman, Ar-Rahim, Maliki yawm al-deen

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:14.000
Iyyaka na'budu wa Iyyaka nasta'iin

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Ihdina siraqa al-mustaqeem

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:21.000
Siraqa al-ladeen an'ante alayhim

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Ghayri al-marzoob alayhim

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:34.390
Assalamu alaikum wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuhu

00:00:34.390 --> 00:00:37.640
Bismillah, Ar-Rahman, Ar-Rahim

00:00:37.640 --> 00:00:39.640
Alhamdulillah, Rabbul Alamin

00:00:39.640 --> 00:00:41.640
Wa bihi nasta'iin, wa nusalli wa nusallim

00:00:41.640 --> 00:00:43.640
Wa ala afzalil khalqi ajmaeen

00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:46.640
Nabi'ina Muhammadin wa ala alihi wa sahbihi wa ttabi'een

00:00:46.640 --> 00:00:49.640
Wa man tabi'ahum bi ihsanin ila yawm al-deen

00:00:49.640 --> 00:00:51.640
We praise Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:00:51.640 --> 00:00:55.640
We send blessings and salutations upon Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:00:55.640 --> 00:00:56.640
And all his companions

00:00:56.640 --> 00:00:59.640
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them all

00:00:59.640 --> 00:01:03.640
And may he bless all those who have struggled and strived from the beginning

00:01:03.640 --> 00:01:05.640
In a way that the deen has come to us

00:01:05.640 --> 00:01:10.640
And may he bless us and make us from amongst those who can learn

00:01:10.640 --> 00:01:15.640
Put into practice and convey the message in a way that our children can also be upon the deen

00:01:15.640 --> 00:01:17.640
And our progenies to come

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:20.640
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us all steadfastness

00:01:20.640 --> 00:01:22.640
And grant us all acceptance, ameen

00:01:22.640 --> 00:01:25.640
Beloved brothers and sisters in Islam

00:01:25.640 --> 00:01:32.640
As you have heard, we have already completed the recitation of more than half of the Quran

00:01:32.640 --> 00:01:34.640
Just yesterday we were starting

00:01:34.640 --> 00:01:38.640
And I remember making mention of the fact that before you know it

00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:40.640
The month will come to an end, believe me

00:01:40.640 --> 00:01:43.640
It is now the second half of this month of Ramadan

00:01:43.640 --> 00:01:46.640
In terms of recitation of the Quran

00:01:46.640 --> 00:01:49.640
And there are a few days left

00:01:49.640 --> 00:01:53.640
In which we need to make use of the spirituality

00:01:53.640 --> 00:01:56.640
And the value of this month of Ramadan

00:01:56.640 --> 00:01:59.640
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala not make us lazy

00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:03.640
And may he make us from amongst those whom when Ramadan finishes

00:02:03.640 --> 00:02:06.640
At least we will be able to say that

00:02:06.640 --> 00:02:10.640
Alhamdulillah, I did not waste my time this month of Ramadan

00:02:10.640 --> 00:02:16.640
And inshallah, every month of Ramadan that we may get to see thereafter

00:02:16.640 --> 00:02:19.640
May Allah make it even better than the previous one, ameen

00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:26.050
We look at a very very important incident that occurred

00:02:26.050 --> 00:02:30.050
To one of the sahaba of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:02:30.050 --> 00:02:32.050
By the name of Salman al-Farisi

00:02:32.050 --> 00:02:36.050
And I'm starting this story because some people had asked me about it

00:02:36.050 --> 00:02:40.050
And we had made mention of Abdullah ibn Salam and how he accepted Islam

00:02:40.050 --> 00:02:44.050
And it's important for us to speak about another companion

00:02:44.050 --> 00:02:47.050
A great companion of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:02:47.050 --> 00:02:50.050
Who was of Persian origin

00:02:50.050 --> 00:02:53.050
And he accepted Islam, what was his journey?

00:02:53.050 --> 00:02:55.050
Many lessons to be learnt

00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:58.050
Salman al-Farisi was from Persia

00:02:58.050 --> 00:03:00.050
His father used to worship the fire

00:03:00.050 --> 00:03:04.050
And he was one of those who was the chief of his people

00:03:04.050 --> 00:03:08.050
He was a leader and he used to be responsible

00:03:08.050 --> 00:03:13.050
To ensure that the fire was not turned off or did not go off at all

00:03:13.050 --> 00:03:16.050
So Salman al-Farisi as a young boy

00:03:16.050 --> 00:03:20.050
His father used to tell him sometimes to go and check that the fire doesn't go off

00:03:20.050 --> 00:03:22.050
So he used to go and come

00:03:22.050 --> 00:03:24.050
And his father loved him a lot

00:03:24.050 --> 00:03:26.050
They used to worship the fire

00:03:26.050 --> 00:03:29.050
Never did his father allow him to go out and so on

00:03:29.050 --> 00:03:31.050
So one day when his father told him

00:03:31.050 --> 00:03:34.050
Look, you know, go and check the fire

00:03:34.050 --> 00:03:36.050
And ensure that it is not turned off

00:03:36.050 --> 00:03:38.050
Make sure that it stays and so on

00:03:38.050 --> 00:03:40.050
Imagine they worship the fire

00:03:40.050 --> 00:03:43.050
And they themselves have to make sure that it's lit

00:03:43.050 --> 00:03:44.050
Allahu Akbar

00:03:44.050 --> 00:03:46.050
Allah safeguard us and protect us

00:03:46.050 --> 00:03:49.050
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us the understanding

00:03:49.050 --> 00:03:53.050
That He alone is deserving of all acts of worship

00:03:53.050 --> 00:03:55.050
La ilaha illallah

00:03:55.050 --> 00:03:58.050
Muhammadur Rasulullah sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:03:58.050 --> 00:04:00.050
So on his way back

00:04:00.050 --> 00:04:02.050
He passed by a monastery

00:04:02.050 --> 00:04:05.050
A little place where the priests were

00:04:05.050 --> 00:04:09.050
And he decided to go and see what they're doing in the church

00:04:09.050 --> 00:04:11.050
So as he went in as a young boy

00:04:11.050 --> 00:04:14.050
He watched them, he listened, he witnessed and so on

00:04:14.050 --> 00:04:18.050
And he told himself this is a better religion than my religion

00:04:18.050 --> 00:04:20.050
My religion I'm worshiping the fire

00:04:20.050 --> 00:04:23.050
At least these people are worshiping a god

00:04:23.050 --> 00:04:24.050
Subhanallah

00:04:24.050 --> 00:04:25.050
And they have better teachings

00:04:25.050 --> 00:04:26.050
And he was right

00:04:26.050 --> 00:04:30.050
Christianity definitely far better religion than worshiping the fire

00:04:30.050 --> 00:04:32.050
And at that time it was the religion

00:04:32.050 --> 00:04:34.050
Because it was the time just after

00:04:34.050 --> 00:04:38.050
Isa alaihi wasallam Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam had not yet come

00:04:38.050 --> 00:04:42.050
So he decided to listen when he went back home he was late

00:04:42.050 --> 00:04:44.050
His father asked him what happened

00:04:44.050 --> 00:04:47.050
So he tells his father exactly what happened as a young boy

00:04:47.050 --> 00:04:50.050
Look, I think there is a religion better than our religion

00:04:50.050 --> 00:04:54.050
And I think that these people have much more sense

00:04:54.050 --> 00:04:55.050
And they make a lot of sense

00:04:55.050 --> 00:04:56.050
We are worshiping the fire

00:04:56.050 --> 00:04:59.050
It goes off, we keep it on and so on

00:04:59.050 --> 00:05:03.050
His father was very upset, very angry being one of the leaders

00:05:03.050 --> 00:05:06.050
So he shackled him and he kept him indoors

00:05:06.050 --> 00:05:11.050
And he ensured that this child does not interact with the outside world

00:05:11.050 --> 00:05:14.050
And it so happened that this increased the love

00:05:14.050 --> 00:05:18.050
That Salman al-Farisi had for religion and for the search of the truth

00:05:18.050 --> 00:05:22.050
And within himself he said I am a Christian

00:05:22.050 --> 00:05:26.050
I am a person who follows what I saw that evening

00:05:26.050 --> 00:05:30.050
And thereafter he sent message to some of the priests

00:05:30.050 --> 00:05:32.050
Who used to travel up to Asham

00:05:32.050 --> 00:05:37.050
You know the region that includes Jerusalem and Syria and all these places

00:05:37.050 --> 00:05:41.050
He sent a message to them saying that whenever there is a caravan going

00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:46.050
Take me with, you can kidnap me or you can just come and release me and take me with

00:05:46.050 --> 00:05:49.050
And he let that message get to them

00:05:49.050 --> 00:05:52.050
When they were leaving, caravan was leaving after some time

00:05:52.050 --> 00:05:55.050
They picked him up and they took him with

00:05:55.050 --> 00:05:58.050
And they took him all the way to Asham where he stayed

00:05:58.050 --> 00:06:00.050
And he was very happy, he learnt the religion

00:06:00.050 --> 00:06:06.050
Imagine he was the son of a very very influential person, one of the leaders

00:06:06.050 --> 00:06:07.050
It did not deter him

00:06:07.050 --> 00:06:10.050
So he went and he worshipped

00:06:10.050 --> 00:06:14.050
And he noticed that this priest is actually robbing

00:06:14.050 --> 00:06:18.050
And stealing the charities of the people and eating the wealth of the people

00:06:18.050 --> 00:06:22.050
But he kept quiet, he was learning and later on the priest died

00:06:22.050 --> 00:06:25.050
When he died, Salman got up and told some of the people

00:06:25.050 --> 00:06:28.050
Look this person, he was actually a traitor

00:06:28.050 --> 00:06:30.050
He was cheating, he was stealing your wealth

00:06:30.050 --> 00:06:33.050
And I want to show you where he used to hide it

00:06:33.050 --> 00:06:35.050
And when he took them and showed them

00:06:35.050 --> 00:06:38.050
They then crucified this priest of theirs

00:06:38.050 --> 00:06:41.050
And they decided this man was a very bad man

00:06:41.050 --> 00:06:43.050
We don't want to give him a proper burial

00:06:43.050 --> 00:06:46.050
And they were actually very very upset

00:06:46.050 --> 00:06:50.050
And thereafter they appointed a very very good, pious man as their leader

00:06:50.050 --> 00:06:53.050
And he was indeed a very good priest

00:06:53.050 --> 00:06:56.050
And he taught Christianity, Salman and Faris he learnt a lot

00:06:56.050 --> 00:06:58.050
When he died another one came

00:06:58.050 --> 00:07:00.050
In fact when he died, Salman and Faris he went to him

00:07:00.050 --> 00:07:03.050
And told him you were such a good man

00:07:03.050 --> 00:07:05.050
And you know I learnt so much from you

00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:07.050
And you are on such a level of piety

00:07:07.050 --> 00:07:10.050
After you die, who should I go to?

00:07:10.050 --> 00:07:13.050
So he was shown go to such and such a person

00:07:13.050 --> 00:07:14.050
And then the other one died

00:07:14.050 --> 00:07:17.050
And he was shown to go to another one and so on

00:07:17.050 --> 00:07:20.050
And in this way he was then told by one of the priests

00:07:20.050 --> 00:07:23.050
That look, you as a young boy

00:07:23.050 --> 00:07:28.050
If you are given life, you will see the prophet who is coming

00:07:28.050 --> 00:07:31.050
And he is going to come in an area

00:07:31.050 --> 00:07:34.050
That is between the two deserts, the two rocky deserts

00:07:34.050 --> 00:07:36.050
Which has date palms

00:07:36.050 --> 00:07:38.050
And he described Madina Munawwara

00:07:38.050 --> 00:07:41.050
So Salman was a young boy, he had hardly anything

00:07:41.050 --> 00:07:44.050
Because obviously he had given up his home

00:07:44.050 --> 00:07:45.050
He had given up everything

00:07:45.050 --> 00:07:48.050
And he was here learning the religion

00:07:48.050 --> 00:07:50.050
And following Christianity

00:07:50.050 --> 00:07:54.050
It so happened that he sent a message to some of the Arabs

00:07:54.050 --> 00:07:58.050
That if you are going into the Arabian Peninsula

00:07:58.050 --> 00:07:59.050
Please take me with

00:07:59.050 --> 00:08:02.050
And then they surely took him with

00:08:02.050 --> 00:08:06.050
And he gave them whatever little he had for the transport

00:08:07.050 --> 00:08:10.050
But sadly when they got to the middle of the desert

00:08:10.050 --> 00:08:12.050
They changed their tune

00:08:12.050 --> 00:08:14.050
They decided to enslave this man

00:08:14.050 --> 00:08:16.050
And they enslaved Salman al-Farisi

00:08:16.050 --> 00:08:19.050
Took him captive and sold him to some people

00:08:19.050 --> 00:08:20.050
So who purchased him?

00:08:20.050 --> 00:08:22.050
A Jewish man purchased him

00:08:22.050 --> 00:08:26.050
And gave him as a gift to his nephew

00:08:26.050 --> 00:08:28.050
And this is all the plan of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:08:28.050 --> 00:08:30.050
Imagine a free man being enslaved

00:08:30.050 --> 00:08:32.050
And this was the pagan Arab time

00:08:32.050 --> 00:08:35.050
When they used to enslave anyone who was weak

00:08:35.050 --> 00:08:39.050
And who didn't have family or clan to protect him or her

00:08:39.050 --> 00:08:40.050
They used to enslave them

00:08:40.050 --> 00:08:43.050
So when they enslaved this man and sold him to the Jewish man

00:08:43.050 --> 00:08:45.050
Who then gave him to his nephew

00:08:45.050 --> 00:08:48.050
The nephew was from a place known as Yathrib

00:08:48.050 --> 00:08:51.050
Yathrib was Madina Munawwara subhanallah

00:08:51.050 --> 00:08:53.050
Now Salman al-Farisi comes

00:08:53.050 --> 00:08:56.050
And Salman al-Farisi came to Al-Madeen al-Munawwara

00:08:56.050 --> 00:08:58.050
And he was enslaved working in the garden

00:08:58.050 --> 00:09:01.050
And working in the orchard and so on

00:09:01.050 --> 00:09:04.050
And he had his master who was a Jewish man

00:09:04.050 --> 00:09:08.050
Now the last priest who met Salman al-Farisi told him

00:09:08.050 --> 00:09:10.050
That the messenger who is going to come

00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:12.050
He has many signs

00:09:12.050 --> 00:09:16.050
From amongst them he will not eat a charity

00:09:16.050 --> 00:09:18.050
If you give him a charity he won't eat from it

00:09:18.050 --> 00:09:21.050
And if you give him a gift he will eat from it

00:09:21.050 --> 00:09:23.050
And if you notice on his back

00:09:23.050 --> 00:09:26.050
He will have a mark, a seal of prophethood

00:09:26.050 --> 00:09:29.050
That is the sign, it's slightly bigger than a pea

00:09:29.050 --> 00:09:31.050
And it is at the back

00:09:31.050 --> 00:09:34.050
On his back just below that shoulder blade

00:09:34.050 --> 00:09:36.050
Or just nearby there

00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:39.050
So Salman al-Farisi he had heard this

00:09:39.050 --> 00:09:42.050
And subhanallah he was waiting

00:09:42.050 --> 00:09:45.050
And at the same time one day

00:09:45.050 --> 00:09:47.050
As he was busy working

00:09:47.050 --> 00:09:52.050
He heard his master being told by another man

00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:53.050
Who was also Jewish

00:09:53.050 --> 00:09:56.050
That do you know that these people of Madina

00:09:56.050 --> 00:09:57.050
They have now met up with someone

00:09:57.050 --> 00:09:59.050
Whom they are calling a prophet

00:09:59.050 --> 00:10:01.050
And he is going to come here to Madina Munawwara

00:10:01.050 --> 00:10:03.050
And at the moment he is in Quba

00:10:03.050 --> 00:10:05.050
And he is coming to Madina

00:10:05.050 --> 00:10:07.050
So Salman dropped whatever he was doing

00:10:07.050 --> 00:10:09.050
And he was in awe

00:10:09.050 --> 00:10:11.050
And what did he ask?

00:10:11.050 --> 00:10:12.050
What did you say?

00:10:12.050 --> 00:10:14.050
There is a prophet who is coming here?

00:10:14.050 --> 00:10:15.050
Subhanallah

00:10:15.050 --> 00:10:17.050
They told him you carry on with what you are doing

00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:19.050
Who told you to ask questions here?

00:10:19.050 --> 00:10:20.050
No questions asked

00:10:20.050 --> 00:10:22.050
You are a slave, carry on doing what you have to

00:10:22.050 --> 00:10:23.050
And so he continued

00:10:23.050 --> 00:10:26.050
But when the prophet salallahu alayhi was salam came

00:10:26.050 --> 00:10:27.050
Salman al-Farisi

00:10:27.050 --> 00:10:29.050
In his little time that he had had

00:10:29.050 --> 00:10:31.050
He went and he started checking

00:10:31.050 --> 00:10:35.050
He looked, he saw, he asked questions and so on

00:10:35.050 --> 00:10:38.050
And he gave a gift, he gave a charity

00:10:38.050 --> 00:10:41.050
In fact he gave something to Rasulullah salallahu alayhi was salam

00:10:41.050 --> 00:10:43.050
And he said this is a charity for you

00:10:43.050 --> 00:10:45.050
The prophet salallahu alayhi was salam did not eat from it

00:10:45.050 --> 00:10:47.050
He didn't eat from it

00:10:47.050 --> 00:10:48.050
And then he came back and said

00:10:48.050 --> 00:10:49.050
Wait, hang on, I gave you something

00:10:49.050 --> 00:10:51.050
And I said by mistake that it's a charity

00:10:51.050 --> 00:10:52.050
It wasn't a charity

00:10:52.050 --> 00:10:54.050
It's just a gift

00:10:54.050 --> 00:10:55.050
Then he ate from it

00:10:55.050 --> 00:10:58.050
So this, he told himself these are two signs

00:10:58.050 --> 00:11:02.050
Did not eat the charity and he ate the gift from the gift

00:11:02.050 --> 00:11:04.050
Then one day it is reported that he noticed

00:11:04.050 --> 00:11:07.050
When the prophet salallahu alayhi was assisting in some

00:11:07.050 --> 00:11:10.050
Carrying a janaza or something of that nature

00:11:10.050 --> 00:11:13.050
And he noticed on his back, subhanallah

00:11:13.050 --> 00:11:16.050
That yes, there is a seal of prophethood here

00:11:16.050 --> 00:11:18.050
Exactly as described

00:11:18.050 --> 00:11:21.050
And this is when Salman al-Farisi declared aloud

00:11:21.050 --> 00:11:24.050
That I bear witness that there is none worthy of worship

00:11:24.050 --> 00:11:26.050
On the other hand that you are the messenger

00:11:26.050 --> 00:11:27.050
Whom we are all waiting for

00:11:27.050 --> 00:11:30.050
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us the understanding

00:11:30.050 --> 00:11:32.050
So this was Salman al-Farisi

00:11:32.050 --> 00:11:34.050
Look at his journey and look at what had happened

00:11:34.050 --> 00:11:35.050
One more issue

00:11:35.050 --> 00:11:36.050
He was still a slave

00:11:36.050 --> 00:11:38.050
So the prophet salallahu alayhi was salam told him

00:11:38.050 --> 00:11:41.050
Ya Salman, why don't you buy yourself

00:11:41.050 --> 00:11:43.050
Buy your freedom

00:11:43.050 --> 00:11:46.050
So there was a certain amount the Jewish man had asked for

00:11:46.050 --> 00:11:50.050
One narration of the historians makes mention of

00:11:50.050 --> 00:11:53.050
The fact that he said I would like 300 date palms

00:11:53.050 --> 00:11:56.050
So you need to sow those for me and make sure that they grow

00:11:56.050 --> 00:11:58.050
It was very difficult at that time

00:11:58.050 --> 00:12:01.050
Because they would plant and when it grows

00:12:01.050 --> 00:12:04.050
A lot of them would die because of adverse weather conditions and so on

00:12:04.050 --> 00:12:05.050
So what happened?

00:12:05.050 --> 00:12:07.050
The prophet salallahu alayhi was salam told him

00:12:07.050 --> 00:12:10.050
Ya Salman, the little amount that you have of gold

00:12:10.050 --> 00:12:13.050
You can sell it and you will get a certain amount of silver

00:12:13.050 --> 00:12:15.050
That this man is asking for

00:12:15.050 --> 00:12:18.050
And if you were to dig these little holes

00:12:18.050 --> 00:12:21.050
So that we can come in and we will plant

00:12:21.050 --> 00:12:23.050
I will plant these for you

00:12:23.050 --> 00:12:25.050
I will put the seeds myself

00:12:25.050 --> 00:12:27.050
And salallahu alayhi was salam came through

00:12:27.050 --> 00:12:28.050
According to one narration

00:12:28.050 --> 00:12:30.050
And he put all those seeds

00:12:30.050 --> 00:12:32.050
Not a single one of them died

00:12:32.050 --> 00:12:34.050
All 300 had grown

00:12:34.050 --> 00:12:36.050
Salman al-Farisi was a free man

00:12:36.050 --> 00:12:37.050
And this is the man

00:12:37.050 --> 00:12:40.050
The same man whom during the battle of the trench

00:12:40.050 --> 00:12:43.050
It was his view to actually dig the trench

00:12:43.050 --> 00:12:45.050
Around parts of Medina Manawara

00:12:45.050 --> 00:12:47.050
To protect it from the enemy

00:12:47.050 --> 00:12:49.050
As they used to do in Persia

00:12:49.050 --> 00:12:51.050
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:12:51.050 --> 00:12:53.050
And grant us understanding

00:12:53.050 --> 00:12:55.050
Now we get to Medina Manawara

00:12:55.050 --> 00:12:57.050
And the condition of the people

00:12:57.050 --> 00:12:58.050
There were in Medina Manawara

00:12:58.050 --> 00:13:00.050
Several categories of people

00:13:00.050 --> 00:13:02.050
When Muhammad salallahu alayhi was salam had come in

00:13:02.050 --> 00:13:04.050
We made mention of the building of the masjid

00:13:04.050 --> 00:13:05.050
And the little piece of land

00:13:05.050 --> 00:13:07.050
That he had purchased from

00:13:07.050 --> 00:13:11.050
The two orphans of Bani Najjab

00:13:11.050 --> 00:13:14.050
And thereafter he had immediately

00:13:14.050 --> 00:13:17.050
Studied the people in Medina Manawara

00:13:17.050 --> 00:13:20.050
And he found the following

00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:21.050
They were the believers

00:13:21.050 --> 00:13:23.050
Who came from Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:13:23.050 --> 00:13:24.050
And these believers

00:13:24.050 --> 00:13:26.050
Who came from Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:13:26.050 --> 00:13:28.050
They were known as al-Muhajireen

00:13:28.050 --> 00:13:30.050
They were removed from their homes

00:13:30.050 --> 00:13:33.050
Their property was stolen in most cases

00:13:33.050 --> 00:13:35.050
By the people of Quraysh

00:13:35.050 --> 00:13:37.050
Their homes were also stolen

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:39.050
Usurped and so on

00:13:39.050 --> 00:13:41.050
And they were all truthful people

00:13:41.050 --> 00:13:43.050
They were no hypocrites from amongst the Muhajireen

00:13:43.050 --> 00:13:45.050
And one of the reasons was

00:13:45.050 --> 00:13:49.050
That a lot of sacrifice was required

00:13:49.050 --> 00:13:52.050
In order to be a Muslim in Makkah

00:13:52.050 --> 00:13:54.050
So it was difficult for a one

00:13:54.050 --> 00:13:56.050
Who wanted to be a Muslim to be a Muslim

00:13:56.050 --> 00:13:58.050
But it was not difficult for he

00:13:58.050 --> 00:13:59.050
Who did not want to be Muslim

00:13:59.050 --> 00:14:01.050
To remain as a non-Muslim

00:14:01.050 --> 00:14:05.050
So it was only those with sincere hearts

00:14:05.050 --> 00:14:07.050
Whom Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:14:07.050 --> 00:14:08.050
Were the Muhajireen

00:14:08.050 --> 00:14:09.050
And this is why in the Qur'an

00:14:09.050 --> 00:14:11.050
Allah praises them

00:14:11.050 --> 00:14:13.050
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:14:13.050 --> 00:14:17.050
For the poor Muhajireen

00:14:17.050 --> 00:14:21.050
Those who were removed from their homes

00:14:21.050 --> 00:14:23.050
And their property

00:14:23.050 --> 00:14:29.050
They seek favor from Allah

00:14:29.050 --> 00:14:33.050
They seek favor from Allah

00:14:33.050 --> 00:14:35.050
And pleasure

00:14:35.050 --> 00:14:40.050
And they help Allah and His Messenger

00:14:40.050 --> 00:14:45.050
Those are the truthful

00:14:45.050 --> 00:14:49.300
Allah says as for those who made Hijra

00:14:49.300 --> 00:14:51.300
The poor people who had made Hijra

00:14:51.300 --> 00:14:53.300
The Muhajireen

00:14:53.300 --> 00:14:56.300
Those who have been driven out of their homes

00:14:56.300 --> 00:14:59.300
And their wealth was usurped

00:14:59.300 --> 00:15:01.300
And they had made Hijra

00:15:01.300 --> 00:15:03.300
For the pleasure of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:15:03.300 --> 00:15:06.300
Allah says they are the truthful

00:15:06.300 --> 00:15:08.300
They are the ones who are the truthful

00:15:08.300 --> 00:15:10.300
You won't find a hypocrite from amongst them

00:15:10.300 --> 00:15:12.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:15:12.300 --> 00:15:15.300
And may He make us truthful as well

00:15:15.300 --> 00:15:17.300
And thereafter the next category of people

00:15:17.300 --> 00:15:20.300
From amongst the Muslims were the Ansar

00:15:20.300 --> 00:15:23.300
The Ansar were the people of Madinah Munawarah

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:25.300
Who opened their arms and who opened their homes

00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:27.300
And who opened whatever they had had

00:15:27.300 --> 00:15:29.300
In terms of welcome

00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:31.300
To welcome these people who had come

00:15:31.300 --> 00:15:32.300
To welcome the messenger

00:15:32.300 --> 00:15:35.300
And to offer protection of the highest degree

00:15:35.300 --> 00:15:37.300
In the same way they protected themselves

00:15:37.300 --> 00:15:38.300
And their family members

00:15:38.300 --> 00:15:40.300
This was the second category of people

00:15:40.300 --> 00:15:43.300
The third category of people were those who were Mushriks

00:15:43.300 --> 00:15:46.300
And they had still not accepted Islam

00:15:46.300 --> 00:15:49.300
They remained on the religion of their forefathers

00:15:49.300 --> 00:15:50.300
From amongst the Arabs

00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:53.300
And these were some of the people of Madinah Munawarah

00:15:53.300 --> 00:15:54.300
And they were also there

00:15:54.300 --> 00:15:58.300
The next category of people were the Jewish clans

00:15:58.300 --> 00:16:00.300
Mainly made up of three of them

00:16:00.300 --> 00:16:02.300
Banu Qaynuqa

00:16:02.300 --> 00:16:04.300
Banu An-Nadheer

00:16:04.300 --> 00:16:05.300
And Banu Quraiba

00:16:05.300 --> 00:16:06.300
As for Banu Qaynuqa

00:16:06.300 --> 00:16:08.300
They were within Madinah Munawarah

00:16:08.300 --> 00:16:10.300
And the other two, Banu An-Nadheer

00:16:10.300 --> 00:16:11.300
And Banu Quraiba

00:16:11.300 --> 00:16:14.300
They were on the outskirts of Madinah Munawarah

00:16:14.300 --> 00:16:16.300
And these people were people of the book

00:16:16.300 --> 00:16:18.300
They were very very intelligent people

00:16:18.300 --> 00:16:20.300
They, Subhanallah

00:16:20.300 --> 00:16:21.300
Banu Qaynuqa

00:16:21.300 --> 00:16:22.300
And Banu An-Nadheer

00:16:22.300 --> 00:16:24.300
They had treaties with Khazraj

00:16:24.300 --> 00:16:27.300
Treaties of protection with Khazraj

00:16:27.300 --> 00:16:28.300
And as for Banu Quraiba

00:16:28.300 --> 00:16:30.300
They had a treaty with Al-Aws

00:16:30.300 --> 00:16:31.300
So if anyone attacks us

00:16:31.300 --> 00:16:33.300
You know you will come

00:16:33.300 --> 00:16:34.300
And we will protect each other together

00:16:34.300 --> 00:16:35.300
And so on

00:16:35.300 --> 00:16:38.300
That's the type of a treaty that they had had

00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:43.300
And the Jewish people were the business people of the area

00:16:43.300 --> 00:16:45.300
They are the ones who controlled

00:16:45.300 --> 00:16:48.300
The buying and selling of the dates and so on

00:16:48.300 --> 00:16:50.300
They were very very intelligent

00:16:50.300 --> 00:16:52.300
They dealt in interest

00:16:52.300 --> 00:16:56.300
They were the ones who controlled the alcoholic market

00:16:56.300 --> 00:16:59.300
The market of beer and alcohol and wines and so on

00:16:59.300 --> 00:17:02.300
These people although they were not so many in number

00:17:02.300 --> 00:17:04.300
They were controlling the market place

00:17:04.300 --> 00:17:05.300
Subhanallah

00:17:05.300 --> 00:17:08.300
And it is reported that one of the ways of controlling was

00:17:08.300 --> 00:17:12.300
To give the leaders loans

00:17:12.300 --> 00:17:16.300
Which were returnable with a great amount of interest

00:17:16.300 --> 00:17:18.300
So they were always indebted to them

00:17:18.300 --> 00:17:20.300
So they had wealth

00:17:20.300 --> 00:17:21.300
They would give it

00:17:21.300 --> 00:17:23.300
They did not charge interest amongst themselves

00:17:23.300 --> 00:17:24.300
Never

00:17:24.300 --> 00:17:26.300
But they would charge it to others

00:17:26.300 --> 00:17:28.300
In order to make them indebted

00:17:28.300 --> 00:17:29.300
Especially the leaders

00:17:29.300 --> 00:17:32.300
So once the leader of a nation or a group

00:17:32.300 --> 00:17:36.300
Is indebted to people whom he owes double, triple, quadruple

00:17:36.300 --> 00:17:39.300
He will be enslaved forever and ever

00:17:39.300 --> 00:17:43.300
If you take a look at the economic laws of the globe today as well

00:17:43.300 --> 00:17:46.300
It operates more or less on similar lines

00:17:46.300 --> 00:17:49.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala never enslave us economically

00:17:49.300 --> 00:17:53.300
So this was what was going on at that particular time

00:17:53.300 --> 00:17:55.300
When Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam came

00:17:55.300 --> 00:17:58.300
He had to deal with these crises as soon as possible

00:17:58.300 --> 00:18:00.300
Because on one hand

00:18:00.300 --> 00:18:04.300
The kuffar of Quraish they were still gobsmacked

00:18:04.300 --> 00:18:06.300
They did not know what struck them

00:18:06.300 --> 00:18:07.300
They had an idea

00:18:07.300 --> 00:18:12.300
But they still did not digest fully what exactly occurred

00:18:12.300 --> 00:18:14.300
Although there was a lot of talking and bubbling

00:18:14.300 --> 00:18:15.300
Subhanallah

00:18:15.300 --> 00:18:16.300
So in the meantime

00:18:16.300 --> 00:18:19.300
The first thing done by Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:18:19.300 --> 00:18:21.300
Was something known as al-mu'akhah

00:18:21.300 --> 00:18:23.300
Bain al-muhajireena wal-ansar

00:18:23.300 --> 00:18:26.300
He created a brotherhood and a link

00:18:26.300 --> 00:18:29.300
Between the families of the muhajireen

00:18:29.300 --> 00:18:31.300
And the families of the ansar

00:18:31.300 --> 00:18:32.300
What this meant is

00:18:32.300 --> 00:18:35.300
Every household from amongst the people of Madinah

00:18:35.300 --> 00:18:39.300
Had to take in a household from amongst the people of Makkah

00:18:39.300 --> 00:18:42.300
And they had to treat them as real brothers

00:18:42.300 --> 00:18:43.300
Subhanallah

00:18:43.300 --> 00:18:45.300
As family members and even more

00:18:45.300 --> 00:18:50.300
And we will come to see some of what was dictated by Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:18:50.300 --> 00:18:51.300
So what had happened

00:18:51.300 --> 00:18:53.300
A miracle happened

00:18:53.300 --> 00:18:56.300
Because there would have been a great refugee crisis

00:18:56.300 --> 00:18:58.300
If this did not take place

00:18:58.300 --> 00:19:02.300
But divine revelation the instruction of the messenger he says

00:19:02.300 --> 00:19:03.300
Look we don't want to fight

00:19:03.300 --> 00:19:06.300
You cannot choose who is going to go into your home

00:19:06.300 --> 00:19:07.300
We will pick it up

00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:10.300
And we will draw as we said the other day lot

00:19:10.300 --> 00:19:11.300
The names were drawn

00:19:11.300 --> 00:19:15.300
And the next person in line would take that particular family and continue

00:19:15.300 --> 00:19:17.300
What were they to share

00:19:17.300 --> 00:19:19.300
Number one their wealth

00:19:19.300 --> 00:19:21.300
Was to be shared half half

00:19:21.300 --> 00:19:23.300
Whatever you have give half

00:19:23.300 --> 00:19:24.300
And you will keep half

00:19:24.300 --> 00:19:25.300
Subhanallah

00:19:25.300 --> 00:19:26.300
Another thing

00:19:26.300 --> 00:19:27.300
Inheritance

00:19:27.300 --> 00:19:29.300
If anyone had died from amongst them

00:19:29.300 --> 00:19:32.300
This one from Makkah would inherit

00:19:32.300 --> 00:19:33.300
The one from Medina

00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:36.300
As though he was one of the family members

00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:37.300
Subhanallah

00:19:37.300 --> 00:19:39.300
So it was something amazing

00:19:39.300 --> 00:19:41.300
So the Ansar

00:19:41.300 --> 00:19:43.300
They told Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:19:43.300 --> 00:19:45.300
That look we love what has happened

00:19:45.300 --> 00:19:46.300
So much so

00:19:46.300 --> 00:19:49.300
That we are people who are farmers

00:19:49.300 --> 00:19:51.300
And we've got lots of what is known as Nakhil

00:19:51.300 --> 00:19:52.300
The date palms

00:19:52.300 --> 00:19:55.300
So why don't you share even

00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:57.300
Our little farms that we have

00:19:57.300 --> 00:19:59.300
Half half between us

00:19:59.300 --> 00:20:00.300
And the Muhajireen

00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:02.300
Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam said

00:20:02.300 --> 00:20:03.300
No

00:20:03.300 --> 00:20:04.300
Not that

00:20:04.300 --> 00:20:05.300
Subhanallah

00:20:05.300 --> 00:20:06.300
One wonders why

00:20:06.300 --> 00:20:07.300
But let's listen to what he said

00:20:07.300 --> 00:20:09.300
He then said

00:20:09.300 --> 00:20:12.300
Mean the Ansar then made a second offer

00:20:12.300 --> 00:20:13.300
And they said okay

00:20:13.300 --> 00:20:16.300
Let them help us when it comes to the labor

00:20:16.300 --> 00:20:18.300
And the looking after it and so on

00:20:18.300 --> 00:20:20.300
And we will share the prophets half half

00:20:20.300 --> 00:20:21.300
Then he agreed

00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:22.300
Yes that is fine

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:23.300
Subhanallah

00:20:23.300 --> 00:20:24.300
So why didn't he agree

00:20:24.300 --> 00:20:27.300
That the farms went half half

00:20:27.300 --> 00:20:29.300
Because the Ansar were farmers

00:20:29.300 --> 00:20:32.300
They knew a lot about how to farm

00:20:32.300 --> 00:20:34.300
But the Muhajireen knew nothing about farming

00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:35.300
So if they had to take the farms

00:20:35.300 --> 00:20:37.300
There would be no production

00:20:37.300 --> 00:20:39.300
And the produce would be low

00:20:39.300 --> 00:20:40.300
So rather than that

00:20:40.300 --> 00:20:42.300
Keep it in the hands of the experts

00:20:42.300 --> 00:20:43.300
Subhanallah

00:20:43.300 --> 00:20:46.300
But strike the deal where half half

00:20:46.300 --> 00:20:49.300
This is the solution of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:20:49.300 --> 00:20:52.300
The prophet was to be shared half half

00:20:52.300 --> 00:20:55.300
But on the ground the expert were the Ansar

00:20:55.300 --> 00:20:57.300
And the helpers who came to assist

00:20:57.300 --> 00:20:59.300
Were the Muhajireen

00:20:59.300 --> 00:21:00.300
Subhanallah

00:21:00.300 --> 00:21:01.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:21:01.300 --> 00:21:03.300
Grant us a lesson from this

00:21:03.300 --> 00:21:05.300
It is a powerful solution

00:21:05.300 --> 00:21:07.300
That did not spoil the economy

00:21:07.300 --> 00:21:09.300
Of the Muslims of Medina Munawwara

00:21:09.300 --> 00:21:10.300
Not at all

00:21:10.300 --> 00:21:12.300
And the Ansar were not affected by it

00:21:12.300 --> 00:21:15.300
Nor were the Muhajireen and anyone else

00:21:15.300 --> 00:21:16.300
This was the solution of

00:21:16.300 --> 00:21:19.300
Muhammad ibn Abdullah sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:21:19.300 --> 00:21:23.300
We need to make mention some of the companions

00:21:23.300 --> 00:21:26.300
And whom they were paired up with as brothers

00:21:26.300 --> 00:21:29.300
Very important for us to know some of them at least

00:21:29.300 --> 00:21:31.300
So one of the most important people

00:21:31.300 --> 00:21:33.300
Abu Bakr as-Siddiq radiallahu anhu

00:21:33.300 --> 00:21:37.300
He was paired up with a man from amongst the Ansar

00:21:37.300 --> 00:21:38.300
Known as Kharijah

00:21:38.300 --> 00:21:40.300
Ibn Zuhayr radiallahu anhu

00:21:40.300 --> 00:21:42.300
So that was his brother

00:21:42.300 --> 00:21:45.300
And he was known as Akhihi

00:21:45.300 --> 00:21:46.300
A brother of his

00:21:46.300 --> 00:21:49.300
Being fostered, being made a brother

00:21:49.300 --> 00:21:50.300
Because of Hijra

00:21:50.300 --> 00:21:52.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:21:52.300 --> 00:21:54.300
The love for one another

00:21:54.300 --> 00:21:57.300
And then Umar ibn Al-Khattab radiallahu anhu

00:21:57.300 --> 00:22:01.300
He was made a brother of Itbani ibn Malik radiallahu anhu

00:22:01.300 --> 00:22:02.300
From amongst the Ansar

00:22:02.300 --> 00:22:04.300
Abu Ubaid Amir ibn Al-Jarrah

00:22:04.300 --> 00:22:06.300
Was made a brother of Sa'd ibn Mu'adh

00:22:06.300 --> 00:22:08.300
And remember they couldn't choose

00:22:08.300 --> 00:22:09.300
Who they wanted to be with

00:22:09.300 --> 00:22:10.300
It was just their luck

00:22:10.300 --> 00:22:13.300
And this was the choice made by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala for them

00:22:14.300 --> 00:22:17.300
Zubayr ibn Al-Awwam radiallahu anhu

00:22:17.300 --> 00:22:20.300
Was with Salamah ibn Salama radiallahu anhu

00:22:20.300 --> 00:22:22.300
Who was a member of the Ansar

00:22:22.300 --> 00:22:24.300
As for Talhah ibn Ubaid Allah

00:22:24.300 --> 00:22:26.300
He was with Ka'b ibn Malik

00:22:26.300 --> 00:22:28.300
Ka'b ibn Malik radiallahu anhu

00:22:28.300 --> 00:22:30.300
We will get to hear more about him

00:22:30.300 --> 00:22:33.300
When we get to the battle of Tabuk insha'Allah

00:22:33.300 --> 00:22:36.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a lesson

00:22:36.300 --> 00:22:39.300
These were all the helpers of the messenger

00:22:39.300 --> 00:22:41.300
Sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:22:41.300 --> 00:22:44.300
Sa'id ibn Zaid was with one of the reciters of the Quran

00:22:44.300 --> 00:22:47.300
From amongst the Ansar who had a beautiful voice

00:22:47.300 --> 00:22:49.300
And his recitation was so clear

00:22:49.300 --> 00:22:51.300
Ubay ibn Ka'b radiallahu anhu

00:22:51.300 --> 00:22:54.300
So much so that the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:22:54.300 --> 00:22:58.300
Used to love to listen to the recitation of Ubay ibn Ka'b

00:22:58.300 --> 00:22:59.300
radiallahu anhu

00:22:59.300 --> 00:23:01.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:23:01.300 --> 00:23:03.300
Even a portion of that clarity

00:23:03.300 --> 00:23:05.300
And that type of recitation

00:23:05.300 --> 00:23:07.300
And may Allah accept it from us

00:23:07.300 --> 00:23:10.300
Then Mus'ab ibn Umayr radiallahu anhu

00:23:10.300 --> 00:23:11.300
Masha'Allah

00:23:11.300 --> 00:23:12.300
Mus'ab ibn Umayr

00:23:12.300 --> 00:23:14.300
The one from Makkah al-Mukarramah

00:23:14.300 --> 00:23:16.300
Whose family was quite wealthy

00:23:16.300 --> 00:23:18.300
And yet he was expelled from them

00:23:18.300 --> 00:23:22.300
He was paired up with Khalid ibn Zaid al-Ansari radiallahu anhu

00:23:22.300 --> 00:23:25.300
And as for Ammar ibn Yasir who was the slave

00:23:25.300 --> 00:23:27.300
Whose family had been martyred in Makkah

00:23:27.300 --> 00:23:30.300
He was paired up with Hudhayfah ibn al-Yaman

00:23:30.300 --> 00:23:32.300
Hudhayfah ibn al-Yaman radiallahu anhu

00:23:32.300 --> 00:23:36.300
Was that companion who narrated most of the prophecies

00:23:36.300 --> 00:23:38.300
Of Rasulullah sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:23:38.300 --> 00:23:42.300
He was gifted by Allah that he bore in mind

00:23:42.300 --> 00:23:44.300
The prophecies of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:23:44.300 --> 00:23:48.300
To this day we look at the prophecies one by one coming true

00:23:48.300 --> 00:23:51.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a deep understanding

00:23:51.300 --> 00:23:54.300
Most of these narrations of Al-Fitan

00:23:54.300 --> 00:23:58.300
They were narrated by Hudhayfah ibn al-Yaman radiallahu anhu

00:23:58.300 --> 00:24:02.300
And then you have Abu Dharr al-Ghifari radiallahu anhu

00:24:02.300 --> 00:24:04.300
Who was also considered a muhajir

00:24:04.300 --> 00:24:06.300
He had made the Hijra

00:24:06.300 --> 00:24:08.300
He was paired up with Al-Mundhir ibn Amr

00:24:08.300 --> 00:24:10.300
And as for Abdulrahman ibn Awf

00:24:10.300 --> 00:24:13.300
He was with Sa'd ibn al-Rabi' radiallahu anhu

00:24:13.300 --> 00:24:17.300
And then I want to end with one beautiful story

00:24:17.300 --> 00:24:20.300
And making mention of two of these companions

00:24:20.300 --> 00:24:22.300
Who were wonderful people

00:24:22.300 --> 00:24:25.300
Salman al-Farisi radiallahu anhu

00:24:25.300 --> 00:24:27.300
The man we spoke about from Persia

00:24:27.300 --> 00:24:29.300
Who was enslaved and so on

00:24:29.300 --> 00:24:33.300
He was paired up with a person from

00:24:34.300 --> 00:24:37.300
He was paired up with Abu d-Dardaa radiallahu anhu

00:24:37.300 --> 00:24:41.300
And what happened is Salman al-Farisi had had a lot of knowledge

00:24:41.300 --> 00:24:44.300
And his knowledge they used to call him a person

00:24:44.300 --> 00:24:47.300
Who has gathered between Christianity and Islam

00:24:47.300 --> 00:24:48.300
Which means he had both books

00:24:48.300 --> 00:24:53.300
He had read the scriptures of the Christians

00:24:53.300 --> 00:24:56.300
And he followed Christianity quite rigidly

00:24:56.300 --> 00:24:58.300
And thereafter he was a Muslim

00:24:58.300 --> 00:25:00.300
He had accepted Islam

00:25:00.300 --> 00:25:02.300
So Salman al-Farisi radiallahu anhu

00:25:02.300 --> 00:25:04.300
He was with Abu d-Dardaa radiallahu anhu

00:25:04.300 --> 00:25:08.300
And he noticed that Abu d-Dardaa was very very pious

00:25:08.300 --> 00:25:14.300
So pious that sometimes he would forget some of his other rights

00:25:14.300 --> 00:25:17.300
That Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala had ordained

00:25:17.300 --> 00:25:22.300
So when he came home he noticed the wife of Abu d-Dardaa

00:25:22.300 --> 00:25:26.300
She would never ever dress in a way that would be

00:25:26.300 --> 00:25:29.300
Of attraction to her own husband

00:25:29.300 --> 00:25:31.300
Now this, there was a relation between them

00:25:31.300 --> 00:25:33.300
So this is why there was speech between them

00:25:33.300 --> 00:25:35.300
Otherwise there would be no speech between them

00:25:35.300 --> 00:25:37.300
But there was a solid relation

00:25:37.300 --> 00:25:39.300
And obviously the speech was with respect

00:25:39.300 --> 00:25:41.300
Atmos respect

00:25:41.300 --> 00:25:47.300
And at that time still the laws of Hijab were not as strict as later on

00:25:47.300 --> 00:25:51.300
So what had happened is Salman al-Farisi asked her

00:25:51.300 --> 00:25:53.300
What is wrong?

00:25:53.300 --> 00:25:58.300
It seems like your dress code is quite tatty and so on

00:25:58.300 --> 00:26:00.300
She says well your brother Abu d-Dardaa

00:26:00.300 --> 00:26:02.300
He doesn't even really look in our direction

00:26:02.300 --> 00:26:04.300
He doesn't have any need in this dunya

00:26:04.300 --> 00:26:07.300
Which means what rights of his wife does he ever fill?

00:26:07.300 --> 00:26:09.300
He doesn't even look in that direction

00:26:09.300 --> 00:26:11.300
Let's pause for a moment

00:26:11.300 --> 00:26:14.300
How many of us are guilty of that?

00:26:14.300 --> 00:26:15.300
Wallahi it's a fact

00:26:15.300 --> 00:26:18.300
We have our wives and we don't give them importance

00:26:18.300 --> 00:26:22.300
And sometimes we don't look at them with an eye of appreciation

00:26:22.300 --> 00:26:25.300
And sometimes we don't utter words of love

00:26:25.300 --> 00:26:28.300
And words of appreciation that can make them feel

00:26:28.300 --> 00:26:32.300
All the reason to be people who take pride in their dress code

00:26:32.300 --> 00:26:34.300
Because of their husbands

00:26:34.300 --> 00:26:37.300
Sadly today we have turned everything upside down

00:26:37.300 --> 00:26:40.300
So you find a woman dresses when she leaves the house

00:26:40.300 --> 00:26:42.300
Rather than for her husband in the home

00:26:42.300 --> 00:26:44.300
Why? Because the world appreciates her

00:26:44.300 --> 00:26:46.300
But we don't back at home

00:26:46.300 --> 00:26:47.300
This is also the problem

00:26:47.300 --> 00:26:49.300
So this is why it's important for us to know

00:26:49.300 --> 00:26:52.300
In Islam it's supposed to be the other way around

00:26:52.300 --> 00:26:54.300
Appreciation should be within the home

00:26:54.300 --> 00:26:56.300
Such that subhanallah

00:26:56.300 --> 00:27:00.300
The dress code is the most magnificent, most attractive dress

00:27:00.300 --> 00:27:01.300
Within the house

00:27:01.300 --> 00:27:03.300
And when we leave the home we are covered

00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:04.300
Alhamdulillah

00:27:04.300 --> 00:27:07.300
We don't want others to see our wives in the same way

00:27:07.300 --> 00:27:12.300
That we wouldn't like to sit and start glaring at someone else's wife

00:27:12.300 --> 00:27:13.300
Subhanallah

00:27:13.300 --> 00:27:15.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala help us

00:27:15.300 --> 00:27:19.300
Not to look at that which we don't even own

00:27:19.300 --> 00:27:20.300
Doesn't belong to us

00:27:20.300 --> 00:27:22.300
And subhanallah

00:27:22.300 --> 00:27:25.300
By looking at others we do not appreciate what we have

00:27:25.300 --> 00:27:27.300
That's one of the secrets or should I say

00:27:27.300 --> 00:27:30.300
One of the benefits of dressing appropriately is

00:27:30.300 --> 00:27:34.300
That if we were all to dress appropriately

00:27:34.300 --> 00:27:35.300
Like the women folk for example

00:27:35.300 --> 00:27:37.300
All of them were to dress appropriately

00:27:37.300 --> 00:27:42.300
What would the men have to compare their wives with?

00:27:42.300 --> 00:27:43.300
Nothing at all

00:27:43.300 --> 00:27:44.300
Today there is nakedness

00:27:44.300 --> 00:27:46.300
So no matter how pretty your wife is

00:27:46.300 --> 00:27:49.300
You will always bump into someone even prettier

00:27:49.300 --> 00:27:51.300
Then you don't appreciate what you have at home

00:27:51.300 --> 00:27:53.300
But you're not going to get that anyway

00:27:53.300 --> 00:27:54.300
So what happens?

00:27:54.300 --> 00:27:55.300
You are caught in the middle

00:27:55.300 --> 00:27:57.300
You die a sad man

00:27:57.300 --> 00:27:58.300
Allahu Akbar

00:27:58.300 --> 00:28:00.300
Because neither did you make use of what you have

00:28:00.300 --> 00:28:02.300
Nor did you ever get what you wished for

00:28:02.300 --> 00:28:03.300
Allahu Akbar

00:28:03.300 --> 00:28:06.300
We'd rather be people who appreciate what we have

00:28:06.300 --> 00:28:07.300
And be honest

00:28:07.300 --> 00:28:09.300
So Salman al-Farisi, powerful words

00:28:09.300 --> 00:28:12.300
He decided let me correct Abu Darda

00:28:12.300 --> 00:28:15.300
Because one of the points of agreement was that

00:28:15.300 --> 00:28:18.300
We need to advise one another

00:28:18.300 --> 00:28:19.300
We teach one another

00:28:19.300 --> 00:28:21.300
The people who have come, the Muhajireen

00:28:21.300 --> 00:28:22.300
They have knowledge

00:28:22.300 --> 00:28:24.300
They will be teaching the Ansar

00:28:24.300 --> 00:28:25.300
Look at how powerful it was

00:28:25.300 --> 00:28:28.300
So the Ansar helped them in terms of dunya

00:28:28.300 --> 00:28:30.300
And the Muhajireen helped the Ansar

00:28:30.300 --> 00:28:31.300
In terms of the Akhira

00:28:31.300 --> 00:28:33.300
In the sense that they had more Quran

00:28:33.300 --> 00:28:34.300
They had more knowledge

00:28:34.300 --> 00:28:35.300
They would all teach

00:28:35.300 --> 00:28:37.300
And there was a teacher in the home automatically

00:28:37.300 --> 00:28:39.300
Subhanallah

00:28:39.300 --> 00:28:41.300
So Salman al-Farisi

00:28:41.300 --> 00:28:43.300
When Abu Darda came back

00:28:43.300 --> 00:28:44.300
The food was prepared

00:28:44.300 --> 00:28:46.300
And he told Abu Darda

00:28:46.300 --> 00:28:47.300
Let's sit down to eat

00:28:47.300 --> 00:28:49.300
Abu Darda says I'm fasting

00:28:49.300 --> 00:28:52.300
So Salman al-Farisi says well

00:28:52.300 --> 00:28:54.300
I'm not going to eat until you eat

00:28:54.300 --> 00:28:56.300
So you'd better break it

00:28:56.300 --> 00:28:58.300
Subhanallah

00:28:58.300 --> 00:29:00.300
And Abu Darda looks at him

00:29:00.300 --> 00:29:03.300
And then he broke his fast and he began to eat

00:29:03.300 --> 00:29:06.300
He began to eat

00:29:06.300 --> 00:29:08.300
So obviously there must have been something in his heart

00:29:08.300 --> 00:29:09.300
In the heart of Abu Darda

00:29:09.300 --> 00:29:11.300
To say well I'm in a fix here

00:29:11.300 --> 00:29:15.300
I'm going to see what the messenger says about this later on

00:29:15.300 --> 00:29:17.300
But when the evening came

00:29:17.300 --> 00:29:19.300
He had not yet seen the messenger

00:29:19.300 --> 00:29:22.300
And he was standing in Salah

00:29:22.300 --> 00:29:24.300
He wanted to stand in the voluntary prayer

00:29:24.300 --> 00:29:25.300
Extra prayer

00:29:25.300 --> 00:29:26.300
So as he is standing

00:29:26.300 --> 00:29:29.300
Salman al-Farisi comes up to him and says

00:29:29.300 --> 00:29:30.300
Go to bed

00:29:30.300 --> 00:29:33.300
And made sure that he went to bed

00:29:33.300 --> 00:29:34.300
And after some time

00:29:34.300 --> 00:29:36.300
He noticed that this man got up again

00:29:36.300 --> 00:29:37.300
Abu Darda got up again

00:29:37.300 --> 00:29:39.300
And he wanted to start his Salah again

00:29:39.300 --> 00:29:41.300
So Salman al-Farisi says

00:29:41.300 --> 00:29:43.300
Go to bed again

00:29:43.300 --> 00:29:44.300
The second time

00:29:44.300 --> 00:29:45.300
And thereafter

00:29:45.300 --> 00:29:47.300
When a third of the night was remaining

00:29:47.300 --> 00:29:49.300
He got Abu Darda up

00:29:49.300 --> 00:29:50.300
And he says

00:29:50.300 --> 00:29:52.300
You can now fulfill your Salah

00:29:52.300 --> 00:29:53.300
You can now pray

00:29:53.300 --> 00:29:54.300
Then he says

00:29:54.300 --> 00:29:55.300
Oh Abu Darda

00:29:55.300 --> 00:29:56.300
Let me teach you something

00:29:56.300 --> 00:30:00.300
You have a duty unto your Rabb

00:30:00.300 --> 00:30:03.300
You have a duty unto yourself

00:30:03.300 --> 00:30:06.300
You have a duty unto your family

00:30:06.300 --> 00:30:07.300
And so on

00:30:07.300 --> 00:30:10.300
So fulfill the right of everyone

00:30:10.300 --> 00:30:12.300
Don't overdo one

00:30:12.300 --> 00:30:15.300
At the price or at the expense of the other

00:30:15.300 --> 00:30:18.300
So this Abu Darda r.a. heard it

00:30:18.300 --> 00:30:19.300
He understood it

00:30:19.300 --> 00:30:20.300
But in the morning

00:30:20.300 --> 00:30:22.300
He went to Rasulullah s.a.w. and told him

00:30:22.300 --> 00:30:23.300
This is what happened

00:30:23.300 --> 00:30:24.300
Firstly

00:30:24.300 --> 00:30:25.300
The fast

00:30:25.300 --> 00:30:26.300
I had to eat

00:30:26.300 --> 00:30:27.300
Secondly

00:30:27.300 --> 00:30:30.300
The man tells me to sleep and not to pray

00:30:30.300 --> 00:30:31.300
And thirdly

00:30:31.300 --> 00:30:33.300
He comes to give me some speech

00:30:33.300 --> 00:30:34.300
And he told me

00:30:34.300 --> 00:30:37.300
That you have a right

00:30:37.300 --> 00:30:39.300
Or Allah has a right over you

00:30:39.300 --> 00:30:43.300
And so does your own body have a right over you

00:30:43.300 --> 00:30:47.300
And so does your family have a right over you

00:30:47.300 --> 00:30:49.300
So fulfill the rights of everyone

00:30:49.300 --> 00:30:51.300
What is the meaning of this?

00:30:51.300 --> 00:30:52.300
Your body has a right

00:30:52.300 --> 00:30:53.300
You need to rest

00:30:53.300 --> 00:30:54.300
You need to sleep

00:30:54.300 --> 00:30:55.300
You need to eat

00:30:55.300 --> 00:30:56.300
You need to make sure

00:30:56.300 --> 00:30:57.300
That you look after this body

00:30:57.300 --> 00:30:59.300
Which is an amana

00:30:59.300 --> 00:31:02.300
Which is a trust from Allah s.w.t.

00:31:02.300 --> 00:31:03.300
If you were not to eat

00:31:03.300 --> 00:31:04.300
Not to rest

00:31:04.300 --> 00:31:05.300
You get sick

00:31:05.300 --> 00:31:06.300
When you are sick and ill

00:31:06.300 --> 00:31:07.300
How are you going to pray?

00:31:07.300 --> 00:31:08.300
So you'd rather be a balanced person

00:31:08.300 --> 00:31:10.300
The same applies to your Rabb

00:31:10.300 --> 00:31:11.300
You can pray MashaAllah

00:31:11.300 --> 00:31:13.300
But not at the expense of your own health

00:31:13.300 --> 00:31:14.300
Because then tomorrow

00:31:14.300 --> 00:31:15.300
You won't be able to pray

00:31:15.300 --> 00:31:17.300
What's the point of doing everything today?

00:31:17.300 --> 00:31:18.300
It's like us

00:31:18.300 --> 00:31:19.300
Sometimes we feel pious

00:31:19.300 --> 00:31:21.300
So we sit with the Quran for two hours

00:31:21.300 --> 00:31:22.300
And then for two months

00:31:22.300 --> 00:31:23.300
We didn't even see one page

00:31:23.300 --> 00:31:24.300
It happens

00:31:24.300 --> 00:31:26.300
We sit in the month of Ramadan

00:31:26.300 --> 00:31:27.300
And MashaAllah

00:31:27.300 --> 00:31:28.300
We make ibadah such

00:31:28.300 --> 00:31:29.300
That people then think

00:31:29.300 --> 00:31:30.300
That you know what

00:31:30.300 --> 00:31:31.300
For the whole month

00:31:31.300 --> 00:31:32.300
Now I don't have to make ibadah

00:31:32.300 --> 00:31:33.300
Or for the whole year

00:31:33.300 --> 00:31:34.300
Sorry

00:31:34.300 --> 00:31:35.300
I now don't have to pray

00:31:35.300 --> 00:31:36.300
You know on a lighter note

00:31:36.300 --> 00:31:37.300
Something comes to my mind

00:31:37.300 --> 00:31:38.300
There was once a lady

00:31:38.300 --> 00:31:40.300
Who had come visiting

00:31:40.300 --> 00:31:41.300
And there was a wedding

00:31:41.300 --> 00:31:42.300
That she was going to be

00:31:42.300 --> 00:31:43.300
Participating in

00:31:43.300 --> 00:31:45.300
So she was making wudhu

00:31:45.300 --> 00:31:46.300
One wudhu

00:31:46.300 --> 00:31:47.300
Two wudhu

00:31:47.300 --> 00:31:48.300
Three wudhu

00:31:48.300 --> 00:31:49.300
Four wudhu

00:31:49.300 --> 00:31:50.300
Five wudhu

00:31:50.300 --> 00:31:51.300
And so she was asked

00:31:51.300 --> 00:31:52.300
What are you doing?

00:31:52.300 --> 00:31:53.300
She says no

00:31:53.300 --> 00:31:54.300
Three, four days

00:31:54.300 --> 00:31:55.300
I'm not going to get a chance

00:31:55.300 --> 00:31:56.300
To make wudhu

00:31:56.300 --> 00:31:57.300
So I'd rather make 10, 15 now

00:31:57.300 --> 00:31:58.300
And then when one breaks

00:31:58.300 --> 00:31:59.300
What will happen is

00:31:59.300 --> 00:32:00.300
I'll still have another wudhu

00:32:00.300 --> 00:32:01.300
Allahu Akbar

00:32:01.300 --> 00:32:02.300
It doesn't work that way

00:32:02.300 --> 00:32:04.300
You make wudhu when the time comes

00:32:04.300 --> 00:32:06.300
You can't read all your prayers

00:32:06.300 --> 00:32:08.300
You can't read all your Salah today

00:32:08.300 --> 00:32:09.300
And say right now for the month

00:32:09.300 --> 00:32:10.300
I'm not going to be able to read

00:32:10.300 --> 00:32:12.300
So I'd rather just read everything

00:32:12.300 --> 00:32:13.300
So this is what

00:32:13.300 --> 00:32:15.300
Abu Darda was being told

00:32:15.300 --> 00:32:17.300
In a much more beautiful way

00:32:17.300 --> 00:32:19.300
To say that this is the right

00:32:19.300 --> 00:32:21.300
Your spouse, your family has a right

00:32:21.300 --> 00:32:23.300
If you don't smile at your wife

00:32:23.300 --> 00:32:24.300
What? You want the neighbor

00:32:24.300 --> 00:32:26.300
To come and quickly smile at her

00:32:26.300 --> 00:32:28.300
Allah protect us

00:32:28.300 --> 00:32:30.300
If you do not talk to her

00:32:30.300 --> 00:32:31.300
With good words

00:32:31.300 --> 00:32:33.300
Who do you want to talk to her

00:32:33.300 --> 00:32:34.300
With good words?

00:32:34.300 --> 00:32:35.300
And I'd better also say

00:32:35.300 --> 00:32:36.300
On the other side of it

00:32:36.300 --> 00:32:37.300
Because people nowadays

00:32:37.300 --> 00:32:39.300
Also suffer the other way

00:32:39.300 --> 00:32:40.300
The women need to know

00:32:40.300 --> 00:32:42.300
That if they are not going to be

00:32:42.300 --> 00:32:44.300
The sweetest to their own husbands

00:32:44.300 --> 00:32:46.300
Then there will be others out there

00:32:46.300 --> 00:32:47.300
Who may be sweet to them

00:32:47.300 --> 00:32:49.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:32:49.300 --> 00:32:51.300
Protect us from shaitan

00:32:51.300 --> 00:32:52.300
Really

00:32:52.300 --> 00:32:53.300
So when you fulfill

00:32:53.300 --> 00:32:55.300
The rights of one another properly

00:32:55.300 --> 00:32:56.300
You resolve your matters

00:32:56.300 --> 00:32:57.300
Without even realizing

00:32:57.300 --> 00:33:00.300
Today we want to over punish

00:33:00.300 --> 00:33:01.300
Even when we punish

00:33:01.300 --> 00:33:02.300
Our own children sometimes

00:33:02.300 --> 00:33:03.300
Or admonish them

00:33:03.300 --> 00:33:04.300
Sometimes we overdo it

00:33:04.300 --> 00:33:06.300
The same applies to our spouses

00:33:06.300 --> 00:33:08.300
If they've done something wrong

00:33:08.300 --> 00:33:09.300
We get so excited

00:33:09.300 --> 00:33:11.300
That we've made a mountain

00:33:11.300 --> 00:33:13.300
Out of a little mole hill

00:33:13.300 --> 00:33:14.300
Let me quickly inform you

00:33:14.300 --> 00:33:15.300
Subhanallah

00:33:15.300 --> 00:33:16.300
When we get married

00:33:16.300 --> 00:33:19.300
If the spouse makes one mistake

00:33:19.300 --> 00:33:21.300
Does that mean the marriage must end?

00:33:21.300 --> 00:33:22.300
No

00:33:22.300 --> 00:33:24.300
The previous generations used to

00:33:24.300 --> 00:33:26.300
Help each other through difficulty

00:33:26.300 --> 00:33:27.300
With us today

00:33:27.300 --> 00:33:28.300
One difficulty

00:33:28.300 --> 00:33:29.300
The person wants out

00:33:29.300 --> 00:33:30.300
No, I'm going

00:33:30.300 --> 00:33:31.300
Why? Because there's one problem

00:33:31.300 --> 00:33:32.300
How foolish is that?

00:33:32.300 --> 00:33:34.300
If we had to break marriages

00:33:34.300 --> 00:33:36.300
Because of a problem or a difficulty

00:33:36.300 --> 00:33:38.300
Everyone's marriages would be broken

00:33:38.300 --> 00:33:40.300
Because everyone has gone through

00:33:40.300 --> 00:33:41.300
Some difficulty or some problem

00:33:41.300 --> 00:33:43.300
So foolish are those

00:33:43.300 --> 00:33:44.300
Who want to break their marriages

00:33:44.300 --> 00:33:46.300
Because of one, two little issues

00:33:46.300 --> 00:33:47.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:33:47.300 --> 00:33:50.300
Make us realize that a spouse

00:33:50.300 --> 00:33:51.300
Is all about support

00:33:51.300 --> 00:33:54.300
And marriage is all about sacrifice

00:33:54.300 --> 00:33:55.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:33:55.300 --> 00:33:56.300
Open our doors

00:33:56.300 --> 00:33:57.300
Make us the best of people

00:33:57.300 --> 00:33:58.300
Remember

00:33:58.300 --> 00:33:59.300
Don't be from amongst those

00:33:59.300 --> 00:34:01.300
Who loses the family life

00:34:01.300 --> 00:34:02.300
And at the same time

00:34:02.300 --> 00:34:04.300
They are vying for something

00:34:04.300 --> 00:34:06.300
Which they will never ever get

00:34:06.300 --> 00:34:07.300
Because they're just looking

00:34:07.300 --> 00:34:08.300
And wishing

00:34:08.300 --> 00:34:09.300
Allahu Akbar

00:34:09.300 --> 00:34:10.300
May Allah protect us

00:34:10.300 --> 00:34:11.300
We need to lower our gaze

00:34:11.300 --> 00:34:13.300
And work on our conditions

00:34:13.300 --> 00:34:14.300
And our family members

00:34:14.300 --> 00:34:15.300
And we will achieve the pleasure

00:34:15.300 --> 00:34:16.300
Of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:34:16.300 --> 00:34:17.300
So

00:34:17.300 --> 00:34:19.300
The Prophet salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:34:19.300 --> 00:34:21.300
Tells Abu Darda two words

00:34:21.300 --> 00:34:23.300
Sadaqa Salman

00:34:23.300 --> 00:34:24.300
Over

00:34:24.300 --> 00:34:26.300
Salman has spoken the truth

00:34:26.300 --> 00:34:27.300
That's it

00:34:27.300 --> 00:34:28.300
Imagine

00:34:28.300 --> 00:34:29.300
After the whole story

00:34:29.300 --> 00:34:30.300
Was put in front of Muhammad

00:34:30.300 --> 00:34:31.300
Salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:34:31.300 --> 00:34:32.300
He just said

00:34:32.300 --> 00:34:34.300
Salman has spoken the truth

00:34:34.300 --> 00:34:35.300
Now the reason I raise this

00:34:35.300 --> 00:34:36.300
Is to show you

00:34:36.300 --> 00:34:38.300
That even amongst ourselves

00:34:38.300 --> 00:34:39.300
We need to help each other

00:34:39.300 --> 00:34:41.300
Where people are going wrong

00:34:41.300 --> 00:34:42.300
And at the same time

00:34:42.300 --> 00:34:43.300
Don't feel bad

00:34:43.300 --> 00:34:44.300
When someone corrects you

00:34:44.300 --> 00:34:45.300
When someone rectifies

00:34:45.300 --> 00:34:46.300
My brother

00:34:46.300 --> 00:34:47.300
Do you know what

00:34:47.300 --> 00:34:48.300
I notice this and that

00:34:48.300 --> 00:34:49.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:34:49.300 --> 00:34:50.300
Grant us goodness

00:34:50.300 --> 00:34:51.300
And these were

00:34:51.300 --> 00:34:53.300
The type of people

00:34:53.300 --> 00:34:55.300
The muhajireen and ansar

00:34:55.300 --> 00:34:56.300
Where they developed

00:34:56.300 --> 00:34:57.300
And subhanallah

00:34:57.300 --> 00:34:58.300
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:34:58.300 --> 00:34:59.300
Granted them

00:34:59.300 --> 00:35:00.300
A lot

00:35:00.300 --> 00:35:01.300
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:35:01.300 --> 00:35:02.300
Opened their doors

00:35:02.300 --> 00:35:03.300
In the dunya

00:35:03.300 --> 00:35:06.300
As well as in the akhirah

00:35:06.300 --> 00:35:08.300
So the issue of inheritance

00:35:08.300 --> 00:35:09.300
Where they used to inherit

00:35:09.300 --> 00:35:10.300
From one another

00:35:10.300 --> 00:35:11.300
That came to an end

00:35:11.300 --> 00:35:13.300
When the verses were revealed

00:35:13.300 --> 00:35:15.300
Where Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala says

00:35:15.300 --> 00:35:18.300
Wa ulul arhaa mi ba'duhum

00:35:18.300 --> 00:35:20.300
Aula bi ba'din

00:35:20.300 --> 00:35:24.300
Fi kitabillah

00:35:24.300 --> 00:35:25.300
When that verse was revealed

00:35:25.300 --> 00:35:26.300
Meaning

00:35:26.300 --> 00:35:28.300
That your family members

00:35:28.300 --> 00:35:30.300
And those who are related to you

00:35:30.300 --> 00:35:31.300
Are closer to you

00:35:31.300 --> 00:35:33.300
In the book of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:35:33.300 --> 00:35:35.300
Than those who made the hijra

00:35:35.300 --> 00:35:37.300
When that verse was revealed

00:35:37.300 --> 00:35:39.300
Referring to inheritance

00:35:39.300 --> 00:35:40.300
Then the inheritance

00:35:40.300 --> 00:35:42.300
Between the muhajireen and ansar

00:35:42.300 --> 00:35:45.300
Had stopped at that particular point

00:35:45.300 --> 00:35:47.300
So this was as far as the brotherhood

00:35:47.300 --> 00:35:49.300
And the relation had gone

00:35:49.300 --> 00:35:50.300
It worked so well

00:35:50.300 --> 00:35:52.300
The sahaba radi allahu anhum

00:35:52.300 --> 00:35:53.300
Who had come from

00:35:53.300 --> 00:35:54.300
Makkat al-Mukarrama

00:35:54.300 --> 00:35:56.300
Many of them were business people

00:35:56.300 --> 00:35:57.300
And the ansar

00:35:57.300 --> 00:35:59.300
They knew much about their farming and so on

00:35:59.300 --> 00:36:01.300
So these business people

00:36:01.300 --> 00:36:03.300
Instead of taking handouts

00:36:03.300 --> 00:36:04.300
A lot of them said

00:36:04.300 --> 00:36:06.300
Show us where the market place is

00:36:06.300 --> 00:36:07.300
They went to the market place

00:36:07.300 --> 00:36:09.300
They came back at the end of the day

00:36:09.300 --> 00:36:12.300
With much more than had been expected

00:36:12.300 --> 00:36:13.300
Subhanallah

00:36:13.300 --> 00:36:16.300
So they did not depend on handouts

00:36:16.300 --> 00:36:19.300
Now we take a look at

00:36:19.300 --> 00:36:23.300
The charter of Madina Munawwara

00:36:23.300 --> 00:36:25.300
The Prophet salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:36:25.300 --> 00:36:26.300
Being made a leader

00:36:26.300 --> 00:36:28.300
He was now the supreme leader

00:36:28.300 --> 00:36:31.300
Spiritually as well as on the ground

00:36:31.300 --> 00:36:33.300
He had political leadership

00:36:33.300 --> 00:36:34.300
In Madina Munawwara

00:36:34.300 --> 00:36:35.300
Subhanallah

00:36:35.300 --> 00:36:36.300
They looked up to him

00:36:36.300 --> 00:36:37.300
He was the decider

00:36:37.300 --> 00:36:38.300
There was one problem

00:36:38.300 --> 00:36:39.300
What was it?

00:36:39.300 --> 00:36:41.300
Before the agreement with

00:36:41.300 --> 00:36:43.300
Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:36:43.300 --> 00:36:44.300
There was a huge war

00:36:44.300 --> 00:36:46.300
Where a lot of the leaders had died

00:36:46.300 --> 00:36:48.300
We made mention of it twice so far

00:36:48.300 --> 00:36:50.300
And as a result

00:36:50.300 --> 00:36:53.300
They were about to appoint a new leader

00:36:54.300 --> 00:36:58.300
Abu Amir al-Rahib or Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salul

00:36:58.300 --> 00:37:02.300
These were the two whom the choice had come down to

00:37:02.300 --> 00:37:04.300
Salul was a man from Khazraj

00:37:04.300 --> 00:37:08.300
And Abu Amir al-Rahib was a man from Al-Aws

00:37:08.300 --> 00:37:12.300
And after much deliberation

00:37:12.300 --> 00:37:16.300
They decided we are going to appoint

00:37:16.300 --> 00:37:18.300
We are going to appoint

00:37:18.300 --> 00:37:21.300
Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salul as our leader

00:37:22.300 --> 00:37:24.300
But before they actually appointed him

00:37:24.300 --> 00:37:26.300
They struck a deal with Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:37:26.300 --> 00:37:27.300
To come to Madina

00:37:27.300 --> 00:37:28.300
The Hijra took place

00:37:28.300 --> 00:37:30.300
And Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam was the leader

00:37:30.300 --> 00:37:35.300
So Ubayy ibn Salul always hated Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:37:35.300 --> 00:37:37.300
Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salul

00:37:37.300 --> 00:37:38.300
He was from Khazraj

00:37:38.300 --> 00:37:40.300
He hated Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:37:40.300 --> 00:37:42.300
Because he was supposed to be a leader

00:37:42.300 --> 00:37:44.300
Almost a king virtually

00:37:44.300 --> 00:37:47.300
And he was the one who was going to be the man

00:37:47.300 --> 00:37:48.300
So because of that

00:37:48.300 --> 00:37:50.300
He did not like Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:37:50.300 --> 00:37:53.300
And those people whom he was going to appoint

00:37:53.300 --> 00:37:55.300
In positions of power

00:37:55.300 --> 00:37:57.300
They also did not like Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasalam

00:37:57.300 --> 00:37:58.300
At this stage

00:37:58.300 --> 00:38:02.300
He was not yet from amongst those who had said the Shahadah

00:38:02.300 --> 00:38:04.300
He was still a pure mushrik

00:38:04.300 --> 00:38:08.300
Later on he saw that it's going to be tough

00:38:08.300 --> 00:38:09.300
I'm going to lose

00:38:09.300 --> 00:38:11.300
As it is I'm not going to be the leader

00:38:11.300 --> 00:38:13.300
And now if I remain as a mushrik

00:38:13.300 --> 00:38:16.300
I'm going to be a person who's going to lose a lot

00:38:16.300 --> 00:38:19.300
So the best bet is for me to pretend like I'm a Muslim

00:38:20.300 --> 00:38:22.300
I can just say that I bear witness

00:38:22.300 --> 00:38:23.300
I will mix with them

00:38:23.300 --> 00:38:24.300
I will be with them

00:38:24.300 --> 00:38:25.300
And wherever I can

00:38:25.300 --> 00:38:27.300
I will try and look at my own benefit

00:38:27.300 --> 00:38:28.300
Remember

00:38:28.300 --> 00:38:30.300
When we look at personal benefit

00:38:30.300 --> 00:38:33.300
We lose the collective benefit

00:38:33.300 --> 00:38:34.300
Take a look at any nation

00:38:34.300 --> 00:38:37.300
If you find corrupt leaders

00:38:37.300 --> 00:38:39.300
You will find the nation is suffering

00:38:39.300 --> 00:38:42.300
But if you find people who are

00:38:42.300 --> 00:38:44.300
Bothered about the collective benefit

00:38:44.300 --> 00:38:46.300
Then everyone will be benefiting

00:38:46.300 --> 00:38:47.300
Mashallah

00:38:47.300 --> 00:38:48.300
So the same applies here

00:38:48.300 --> 00:38:53.300
This man was bothered about his own personal benefit and gain

00:38:53.300 --> 00:38:55.300
And he was not really bothered about the others

00:38:55.300 --> 00:38:57.300
This was Abdullah ibn Ubayy ibn Salul

00:38:57.300 --> 00:38:59.300
Now the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:38:59.300 --> 00:39:02.300
Had to strike two agreements

00:39:02.300 --> 00:39:04.300
One was amongst the believers

00:39:04.300 --> 00:39:06.300
We need to strike an agreement

00:39:06.300 --> 00:39:07.300
We need to write something down

00:39:07.300 --> 00:39:08.300
He was a leader

00:39:08.300 --> 00:39:10.300
And when we write something down

00:39:10.300 --> 00:39:14.300
Everybody must pledge allegiance upon that

00:39:14.300 --> 00:39:15.300
And secondly

00:39:15.300 --> 00:39:17.300
We need to sign a treaty

00:39:17.300 --> 00:39:19.300
We are not Muslims around us

00:39:19.300 --> 00:39:20.300
They are Jewish people

00:39:20.300 --> 00:39:21.300
And they are the others

00:39:21.300 --> 00:39:22.300
We need to strike a treaty with them

00:39:22.300 --> 00:39:24.300
We cannot be seen to be at war

00:39:24.300 --> 00:39:26.300
With anyone and everyone around here

00:39:26.300 --> 00:39:28.300
And there would be no reason for us

00:39:28.300 --> 00:39:30.300
To be at war with them

00:39:30.300 --> 00:39:32.300
So the first thing he did

00:39:32.300 --> 00:39:33.300
He struck this treaty

00:39:33.300 --> 00:39:34.300
The Charter of Madina

00:39:34.300 --> 00:39:36.300
وثيقة المدينة المنورة

00:39:36.300 --> 00:39:37.300
We ask Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:39:37.300 --> 00:39:39.300
To grant us lesson from it

00:39:39.300 --> 00:39:42.300
I am going to mention a few points

00:39:42.300 --> 00:39:43.300
From the agreement

00:39:43.300 --> 00:39:45.300
That was struck amongst the believers

00:39:45.300 --> 00:39:46.300
Remember

00:39:46.300 --> 00:39:48.300
We are building a nation here

00:39:48.300 --> 00:39:49.300
So this is a Charter

00:39:49.300 --> 00:39:50.300
There were so many points

00:39:50.300 --> 00:39:51.300
We don't have the time

00:39:51.300 --> 00:39:53.300
To go through every single one of them

00:39:53.300 --> 00:39:54.300
But some of them

00:39:54.300 --> 00:39:55.300
And as I said

00:39:55.300 --> 00:39:56.300
We're building a nation

00:39:56.300 --> 00:39:59.300
So one of the first points

00:39:59.300 --> 00:40:00.300
The Mu'mineen

00:40:00.300 --> 00:40:03.300
They are one nation

00:40:03.300 --> 00:40:05.300
And all those who are here

00:40:05.300 --> 00:40:06.300
In Madina Munawwara

00:40:06.300 --> 00:40:08.300
Will be part of the nation

00:40:08.300 --> 00:40:09.300
So the Mu'mineen

00:40:09.300 --> 00:40:10.300
They are one nation

00:40:10.300 --> 00:40:12.300
Those who are in Madina Munawwara

00:40:12.300 --> 00:40:13.300
Are part of the nation

00:40:13.300 --> 00:40:15.300
And they are preferred

00:40:15.300 --> 00:40:17.300
Over those from outside

00:40:17.300 --> 00:40:18.300
So this would mean a lot

00:40:18.300 --> 00:40:19.300
It has a deep meaning

00:40:19.300 --> 00:40:21.300
Because we come first

00:40:21.300 --> 00:40:22.300
If I am to help

00:40:22.300 --> 00:40:23.300
We help one another

00:40:23.300 --> 00:40:24.300
Anyone from outside

00:40:24.300 --> 00:40:25.300
We help him after

00:40:25.300 --> 00:40:26.300
We've helped you

00:40:26.300 --> 00:40:27.300
And thereafter

00:40:27.300 --> 00:40:29.300
If there is an attack from outside

00:40:29.300 --> 00:40:30.300
We would obviously

00:40:30.300 --> 00:40:32.300
All be protecting one another

00:40:32.300 --> 00:40:33.300
All this came into

00:40:33.300 --> 00:40:35.300
Some of the final clauses

00:40:35.300 --> 00:40:37.300
You look at the next clause

00:40:37.300 --> 00:40:38.300
Which said

00:40:38.300 --> 00:40:40.300
That the blood money

00:40:40.300 --> 00:40:41.300
And the ransom

00:40:41.300 --> 00:40:42.300
That would have to be paid

00:40:42.300 --> 00:40:44.300
By every group

00:40:44.300 --> 00:40:46.300
Would be paid by the group

00:40:46.300 --> 00:40:48.300
And if there was a poor person

00:40:48.300 --> 00:40:50.300
Then we would all come in

00:40:50.300 --> 00:40:52.300
To help that particular poor person

00:40:52.300 --> 00:40:53.300
In order to pay

00:40:53.300 --> 00:40:54.300
Whatever they owe

00:40:54.300 --> 00:40:56.300
And here when we talk of blood money

00:40:56.300 --> 00:40:58.300
This was something at the time

00:40:58.300 --> 00:41:00.300
Where if someone had killed someone

00:41:00.300 --> 00:41:01.300
By mistake

00:41:01.300 --> 00:41:02.300
By error

00:41:02.300 --> 00:41:03.300
If a person was killed by error

00:41:03.300 --> 00:41:06.300
They had to pay some blood money

00:41:06.300 --> 00:41:08.300
That blood money would be paid

00:41:08.300 --> 00:41:10.300
By the family or the clan

00:41:10.300 --> 00:41:12.300
Or the tribe of the person

00:41:12.300 --> 00:41:15.300
Who was guilty of what is known today

00:41:15.300 --> 00:41:16.300
I would like to think

00:41:16.300 --> 00:41:18.300
As culpable homicide

00:41:18.300 --> 00:41:20.300
Where you didn't kill someone intentionally

00:41:20.300 --> 00:41:22.300
But it resulted in murder

00:41:22.300 --> 00:41:24.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us

00:41:24.300 --> 00:41:27.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:41:27.300 --> 00:41:29.300
It is called qatlul khata

00:41:29.300 --> 00:41:31.300
Person who kills someone else by mistake

00:41:31.300 --> 00:41:33.300
Nowadays one of the quickest

00:41:33.300 --> 00:41:35.300
Examples that come to my mind is

00:41:35.300 --> 00:41:36.300
If you're driving a vehicle

00:41:36.300 --> 00:41:37.300
And you make an accident

00:41:37.300 --> 00:41:38.300
And the passengers die

00:41:38.300 --> 00:41:39.300
In actual fact

00:41:39.300 --> 00:41:41.300
The driver is guilty

00:41:41.300 --> 00:41:42.300
Of something, of a crime

00:41:42.300 --> 00:41:44.300
And it's lesser than murder

00:41:44.300 --> 00:41:45.300
But it is actually a crime

00:41:45.300 --> 00:41:47.300
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:41:47.300 --> 00:41:49.300
Goodness and may He protect us all

00:41:49.300 --> 00:41:52.300
Then the Prophet sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:41:52.300 --> 00:41:55.580
Makes mention of another point

00:41:55.580 --> 00:41:57.580
All the believers will be against

00:41:57.580 --> 00:41:59.580
Anyone who has oppressed

00:41:59.580 --> 00:42:01.580
Anyone who transgresses

00:42:01.580 --> 00:42:03.580
And anyone who engages in

00:42:03.580 --> 00:42:05.580
Any form of corruption

00:42:05.580 --> 00:42:07.580
Even if he is a relative

00:42:07.580 --> 00:42:09.580
So if you have a relative

00:42:09.580 --> 00:42:11.580
And he has committed a crime

00:42:11.580 --> 00:42:12.580
Don't protect him

00:42:12.580 --> 00:42:13.580
You need to hand him over

00:42:13.580 --> 00:42:14.580
Subhanallah

00:42:14.580 --> 00:42:15.580
This they all agreed upon

00:42:15.580 --> 00:42:17.580
And then also

00:42:17.580 --> 00:42:19.580
The mu'mineen, their blood

00:42:19.580 --> 00:42:21.580
Is all equal

00:42:21.580 --> 00:42:22.580
The most humble

00:42:22.580 --> 00:42:24.580
All the poorest from amongst them

00:42:24.580 --> 00:42:25.580
The richest from amongst them

00:42:25.580 --> 00:42:27.580
There are no lines

00:42:27.580 --> 00:42:29.580
The blood is equal

00:42:29.580 --> 00:42:31.580
And anyone who is to engage

00:42:31.580 --> 00:42:32.580
In any form of a crime

00:42:32.580 --> 00:42:34.580
They should be handed over

00:42:34.580 --> 00:42:35.580
And on top of that

00:42:35.580 --> 00:42:37.580
Nobody should help

00:42:37.580 --> 00:42:40.580
Anyone else to fight a believer

00:42:40.580 --> 00:42:42.580
And nobody should help

00:42:42.580 --> 00:42:44.580
Even the disbelievers

00:42:44.580 --> 00:42:45.580
To fight the believers

00:42:45.580 --> 00:42:46.580
Who came through

00:42:46.580 --> 00:42:47.580
This was an agreement

00:42:47.580 --> 00:42:48.580
And thereafter

00:42:48.580 --> 00:42:51.580
There was another part of the agreement

00:42:51.580 --> 00:42:53.580
Which said

00:42:53.580 --> 00:42:55.580
The Jewish people around us

00:42:55.580 --> 00:42:57.580
Should not be harmed

00:42:57.580 --> 00:43:00.580
And we should never assist an enemy

00:43:00.580 --> 00:43:01.580
Who comes to attack them

00:43:01.580 --> 00:43:02.580
Look at this

00:43:02.580 --> 00:43:04.580
The Jewish people around us

00:43:04.580 --> 00:43:06.580
Because they are part of the nation

00:43:06.580 --> 00:43:08.580
So when you are a leader of the nation

00:43:08.580 --> 00:43:09.580
You have to look at the others

00:43:09.580 --> 00:43:11.580
Not perhaps on your faith

00:43:11.580 --> 00:43:13.580
And you have to also ensure

00:43:13.580 --> 00:43:14.580
That they are protected

00:43:14.580 --> 00:43:17.580
And so the agreement of Medina

00:43:17.580 --> 00:43:19.580
Amongst the believers was that

00:43:19.580 --> 00:43:21.580
The Jewish people would not be harmed

00:43:21.580 --> 00:43:23.580
And anyone who was coming

00:43:23.580 --> 00:43:25.580
To harm the Jewish people

00:43:25.580 --> 00:43:27.580
Should not be assisted in any way

00:43:27.580 --> 00:43:29.580
And in fact later on even

00:43:29.580 --> 00:43:32.580
There is a point that makes mention of

00:43:32.580 --> 00:43:35.580
The fact that they should be chased away

00:43:35.580 --> 00:43:36.580
They should be fought

00:43:36.580 --> 00:43:37.580
Who should be fought?

00:43:37.580 --> 00:43:39.580
Those who come and attack this nation

00:43:39.580 --> 00:43:41.580
And those who come and attack

00:43:41.580 --> 00:43:43.580
Even if they were to come to attack

00:43:43.580 --> 00:43:44.580
Meaning the Jewish people

00:43:44.580 --> 00:43:46.580
Who were in Medina Munawwara

00:43:46.580 --> 00:43:48.580
The mu'mineen would gather together

00:43:48.580 --> 00:43:50.580
And they would repel that attack

00:43:50.580 --> 00:43:51.580
That was coming from outside

00:43:51.580 --> 00:43:53.580
This is made mention in this

00:43:53.580 --> 00:43:55.580
Watiqatul Medinatul Munawwara

00:43:55.580 --> 00:43:58.580
And then a very important point

00:43:58.580 --> 00:44:02.580
Nobody should have their private peace

00:44:02.580 --> 00:44:04.580
With Quraish

00:44:04.580 --> 00:44:06.580
Nobody is allowed to make peace

00:44:06.580 --> 00:44:09.580
With anyone the mu'mines were at war with

00:44:09.580 --> 00:44:10.580
And this would mean that

00:44:10.580 --> 00:44:12.580
Some people cannot come up and say

00:44:12.580 --> 00:44:13.580
Look I've got my private agreement

00:44:13.580 --> 00:44:14.580
With these people

00:44:14.580 --> 00:44:16.580
So I'm sorry I need to you know

00:44:16.580 --> 00:44:18.580
Fulfill the rights of these people

00:44:18.580 --> 00:44:19.580
Or I need to do this and that

00:44:19.580 --> 00:44:21.580
No, if it is an agreement

00:44:21.580 --> 00:44:23.580
It's an agreement of everyone

00:44:23.580 --> 00:44:24.580
And we are all one

00:44:24.580 --> 00:44:26.580
So nobody can come and say

00:44:26.580 --> 00:44:27.580
No sorry excuse me

00:44:27.580 --> 00:44:29.580
See this is a crisis we face today

00:44:29.580 --> 00:44:32.580
Where you have an oppressor in community

00:44:32.580 --> 00:44:33.580
And you find some people say

00:44:33.580 --> 00:44:34.580
No but you know I have to do this

00:44:34.580 --> 00:44:35.580
Because he's a big businessman

00:44:35.580 --> 00:44:38.580
And I can't you know disassociate from him

00:44:38.580 --> 00:44:39.580
And so on so what we do

00:44:39.580 --> 00:44:41.580
We make him more powerful

00:44:41.580 --> 00:44:42.580
He becomes more powerful

00:44:42.580 --> 00:44:43.580
If everyone was one

00:44:43.580 --> 00:44:45.580
And we all said you are wrong

00:44:45.580 --> 00:44:47.580
No matter how wealthy he was

00:44:47.580 --> 00:44:48.580
He would come with his tail

00:44:48.580 --> 00:44:49.580
Between his legs

00:44:49.580 --> 00:44:51.580
And he would humble himself

00:44:51.580 --> 00:44:52.580
But the problem is

00:44:52.580 --> 00:44:53.580
We are not that united

00:44:53.580 --> 00:44:55.580
As these people at the beginning were

00:44:55.580 --> 00:44:57.580
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala protect us

00:44:57.580 --> 00:44:58.580
And grant us goodness

00:44:58.580 --> 00:45:00.580
Then the next point

00:45:00.580 --> 00:45:02.580
That is made mention of is

00:45:02.580 --> 00:45:04.580
This agreement will not be broken

00:45:04.580 --> 00:45:07.580
All those who believe will make sure

00:45:07.580 --> 00:45:08.580
That they uphold the agreement

00:45:08.580 --> 00:45:10.580
And subhanallah

00:45:10.580 --> 00:45:11.580
If there is any dispute

00:45:11.580 --> 00:45:13.580
It should go straight to the messenger

00:45:13.580 --> 00:45:14.580
Sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:45:14.580 --> 00:45:16.580
So these are just some of the points

00:45:16.580 --> 00:45:17.580
That I've decided to make mention of

00:45:17.580 --> 00:45:19.580
Because this is nation building

00:45:19.580 --> 00:45:22.580
Up to today these points are valid

00:45:22.580 --> 00:45:24.580
If we would like to build a nation

00:45:24.580 --> 00:45:26.580
And if we would like to build a community

00:45:26.580 --> 00:45:28.580
We need to have the kamaradi

00:45:28.580 --> 00:45:29.580
And at the same time

00:45:29.580 --> 00:45:31.580
We need to protect one another

00:45:31.580 --> 00:45:33.580
And we need to have rules that sometimes

00:45:33.580 --> 00:45:36.580
May go against our personal preference

00:45:36.580 --> 00:45:38.580
For the preference of the entire lot

00:45:38.580 --> 00:45:41.580
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:45:41.580 --> 00:45:44.580
Then came the agreement with the Jewish people

00:45:44.580 --> 00:45:46.580
And this was a powerful treaty

00:45:46.580 --> 00:45:49.580
It was known as the treaty with the Jews

00:45:49.580 --> 00:45:52.580
One of the first points

00:45:52.580 --> 00:45:55.580
Was that the Jewish people of this Banu Awf

00:45:55.580 --> 00:45:57.580
Who were the Jews around Medina Munawwara

00:45:57.580 --> 00:45:59.580
They will be considered as one nation

00:45:59.580 --> 00:46:01.580
One nation with the believers

00:46:01.580 --> 00:46:02.580
Subhanallah

00:46:02.580 --> 00:46:03.580
Next point

00:46:03.580 --> 00:46:04.580
They will follow their faith

00:46:04.580 --> 00:46:06.580
And the mu'mineen will follow their faith

00:46:06.580 --> 00:46:09.580
None will cross the lines of the other

00:46:09.580 --> 00:46:10.580
Subhanallah

00:46:10.580 --> 00:46:11.580
Look at this agreement

00:46:11.580 --> 00:46:13.580
Because it was so powerful

00:46:13.580 --> 00:46:17.580
In that even the timing of it was perfect

00:46:17.580 --> 00:46:18.580
If there was a slight delay

00:46:18.580 --> 00:46:20.580
By that time people might have come in

00:46:20.580 --> 00:46:22.580
And the mushriks of Quraysh

00:46:22.580 --> 00:46:23.580
They tried to tamper later on

00:46:23.580 --> 00:46:24.580
It was too late

00:46:24.580 --> 00:46:26.580
There was an agreement in place already

00:46:26.580 --> 00:46:27.580
So Nabi sallallahu alaihi wasallam

00:46:27.580 --> 00:46:28.580
Was very intelligent

00:46:28.580 --> 00:46:29.580
First things first

00:46:29.580 --> 00:46:30.580
Let's sign a treaty with everyone

00:46:30.580 --> 00:46:31.580
Let's make peace here

00:46:31.580 --> 00:46:33.580
And we need to be at peace with everyone

00:46:33.580 --> 00:46:36.580
Then the next point was

00:46:36.580 --> 00:46:39.580
That the mu'mineen

00:46:39.580 --> 00:46:41.580
The believers will be responsible

00:46:41.580 --> 00:46:44.580
For all their living and their costs and so on

00:46:44.580 --> 00:46:47.580
And the Jewish people will be responsible for theirs

00:46:47.580 --> 00:46:49.580
When it comes to war

00:46:49.580 --> 00:46:52.580
The Jewish people will pay

00:46:52.580 --> 00:46:54.580
A part of the expense of the war

00:46:54.580 --> 00:46:56.580
On condition that they are fighting

00:46:56.580 --> 00:46:58.580
Alongside with the believers

00:46:58.580 --> 00:46:59.580
So if they are fighting

00:46:59.580 --> 00:47:00.580
Alongside with the believers

00:47:00.580 --> 00:47:03.580
They must also take some of the burden

00:47:03.580 --> 00:47:04.580
Of the costs of the war

00:47:04.580 --> 00:47:07.580
And thereafter we will fulfill

00:47:07.580 --> 00:47:11.580
This covenant with mutual respect

00:47:11.580 --> 00:47:13.580
Mutually this will be fulfilled

00:47:13.580 --> 00:47:17.580
And we will be righteous with one another

00:47:17.580 --> 00:47:18.580
The next point was

00:47:18.580 --> 00:47:21.580
That none of us should engage

00:47:21.580 --> 00:47:25.580
In any behavior that will undermine the other

00:47:25.580 --> 00:47:28.580
So the Jews were not to engage in behavior

00:47:28.580 --> 00:47:29.580
That would undermine the Muslims

00:47:29.580 --> 00:47:32.580
And the Muslims were not to engage in behavior

00:47:32.580 --> 00:47:34.580
That would undermine the Jews

00:47:34.580 --> 00:47:35.580
This was a powerful point

00:47:35.580 --> 00:47:38.580
And they were very happy about it

00:47:38.580 --> 00:47:41.580
Then anyone who is oppressed from either side

00:47:41.580 --> 00:47:44.580
We will all get up and help him

00:47:44.580 --> 00:47:45.580
Whoever is oppressed

00:47:45.580 --> 00:47:47.580
We will get up and help him

00:47:47.580 --> 00:47:50.580
And then the point that

00:47:50.580 --> 00:47:52.580
Yathrib meaning Madina Munawwara

00:47:52.580 --> 00:47:56.580
It is prohibited to fight within Madina Munawwara

00:47:56.580 --> 00:47:58.580
Completely prohibited

00:47:58.580 --> 00:48:01.580
So within the surroundings of this place

00:48:01.580 --> 00:48:03.580
Known as Madina Munawwara

00:48:03.580 --> 00:48:05.580
It became what is known as Haram

00:48:05.580 --> 00:48:07.580
Haram meaning no fighting in it

00:48:07.580 --> 00:48:09.580
Everyone will be at peace in it

00:48:09.580 --> 00:48:12.580
Just like Mecca was made Haram

00:48:12.580 --> 00:48:14.580
By Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:48:14.580 --> 00:48:17.580
From the time of Ibrahim a.s.

00:48:17.580 --> 00:48:20.580
So Madina Munawwara was made Haram

00:48:20.580 --> 00:48:23.580
Everything in Madina was to be at peace

00:48:23.580 --> 00:48:24.580
No war happening there

00:48:24.580 --> 00:48:26.580
Nobody should be killing each other

00:48:26.580 --> 00:48:28.580
Nothing should happen there

00:48:28.580 --> 00:48:30.580
Which would undermine the peace and security

00:48:30.580 --> 00:48:32.580
Of the people of Madina Munawwara

00:48:32.580 --> 00:48:34.580
So much so that later on the Prophet s.a.w.

00:48:34.580 --> 00:48:37.580
Extended it to even the creatures of Madina Munawwara

00:48:37.580 --> 00:48:39.580
And the plants

00:48:39.580 --> 00:48:42.580
Where you are not allowed to destructively

00:48:42.580 --> 00:48:44.580
Remove plants and so on

00:48:44.580 --> 00:48:46.580
And trees from Madina Munawwara

00:48:46.580 --> 00:48:48.580
And even the little insects and other items

00:48:48.580 --> 00:48:50.580
That you see within the boundaries of the Haram

00:48:50.580 --> 00:48:52.580
We are not allowed to just kill them haphazardly

00:48:52.580 --> 00:48:54.580
Obviously there are certain insects

00:48:54.580 --> 00:48:56.580
That we were permitted to kill

00:48:56.580 --> 00:48:58.580
And certain reptiles and so on

00:48:58.580 --> 00:49:00.580
But besides that we were not permitted

00:49:00.580 --> 00:49:03.580
To even kill the little insects

00:49:03.580 --> 00:49:04.580
Subhanallah

00:49:04.580 --> 00:49:07.580
Everything supposed to be at peace in Madina Munawwara

00:49:07.580 --> 00:49:10.580
And then if there is any dispute

00:49:10.580 --> 00:49:12.580
It will go to Muhammad s.a.w.

00:49:12.580 --> 00:49:15.580
Another important point is

00:49:15.580 --> 00:49:18.580
We will all boycott Quraish

00:49:18.580 --> 00:49:20.580
So like they boycotted us four times

00:49:20.580 --> 00:49:22.580
We will all boycott them, no dealing

00:49:22.580 --> 00:49:24.580
The Jews will not deal with Quraish

00:49:24.580 --> 00:49:26.580
Or anyone who is connected to them

00:49:26.580 --> 00:49:29.580
And the Mu'mineen will not deal with Quraish

00:49:29.580 --> 00:49:32.580
Or anyone who deals with them

00:49:32.580 --> 00:49:34.580
And the next point was

00:49:34.580 --> 00:49:36.580
We will all get up to defend this nation

00:49:36.580 --> 00:49:37.580
Of Madina Munawwara

00:49:37.580 --> 00:49:39.580
So whenever there is an attack from outside

00:49:39.580 --> 00:49:40.580
We are one

00:49:40.580 --> 00:49:43.580
We get together and we fight them together

00:49:43.580 --> 00:49:46.580
May Allah s.w.t. grant us understanding

00:49:46.580 --> 00:49:48.580
See this nation building is a very important point

00:49:48.580 --> 00:49:50.580
It requires a lot of wisdom

00:49:50.580 --> 00:49:52.580
And it requires a lot of tolerance

00:49:52.580 --> 00:49:55.580
And yes when the treaties were broken

00:49:55.580 --> 00:49:58.580
Later on something else happened

00:49:58.580 --> 00:50:00.580
But this was the initial treaty

00:50:00.580 --> 00:50:02.580
And if nobody had broken the treaty

00:50:02.580 --> 00:50:04.580
They would never have had a problem

00:50:04.580 --> 00:50:07.580
The problem was when people began to break the treaty

00:50:07.580 --> 00:50:12.580
And this is when the whole situation took a new twist

00:50:12.580 --> 00:50:15.580
Then we have another very important point

00:50:15.580 --> 00:50:20.580
And that was that this treaty will not hinder

00:50:20.580 --> 00:50:24.580
The lawful revenge against an oppressor

00:50:24.580 --> 00:50:25.580
So if there is an oppressor

00:50:25.580 --> 00:50:26.580
You can't say no no no

00:50:26.580 --> 00:50:27.580
He is from amongst us

00:50:27.580 --> 00:50:28.580
You can't fight him

00:50:28.580 --> 00:50:30.580
No, if he is an oppressor

00:50:30.580 --> 00:50:33.580
Then this treaty excludes that particular person

00:50:33.580 --> 00:50:34.580
Because as you heard earlier

00:50:34.580 --> 00:50:37.580
They would all get up to assist the oppressor

00:50:37.580 --> 00:50:39.580
So now came this nation

00:50:39.580 --> 00:50:40.580
And the nation was being built

00:50:40.580 --> 00:50:41.580
And subhanallah

00:50:41.580 --> 00:50:44.580
Allah s.w.t. granted them great strength

00:50:44.580 --> 00:50:46.580
If you look at Rasulullah s.a.w

00:50:46.580 --> 00:50:48.580
Just to mention a little bit of what he gave

00:50:48.580 --> 00:50:50.580
A lot of importance to

00:50:50.580 --> 00:50:55.580
Firstly education, knowledge, to learn

00:50:55.580 --> 00:50:57.580
And to learn to read and write as well

00:50:57.580 --> 00:51:01.580
Was given a lot of importance by Muhammad s.a.w

00:51:01.580 --> 00:51:02.580
At that time

00:51:02.580 --> 00:51:04.580
So much so that after one of the wars

00:51:04.580 --> 00:51:06.580
He freed people who taught the mu'mineen

00:51:06.580 --> 00:51:07.580
How to read and write

00:51:07.580 --> 00:51:08.580
We will get to that inshallah

00:51:09.580 --> 00:51:12.580
Also the cleansing of the soul

00:51:12.580 --> 00:51:14.580
And the bad qualities of the heart

00:51:14.580 --> 00:51:18.580
Was given great importance by Rasulullah s.a.w

00:51:18.580 --> 00:51:19.580
Good character and conduct

00:51:19.580 --> 00:51:22.580
Love, brotherhood, honor, dignity

00:51:22.580 --> 00:51:25.580
Worship and obedience to Allah s.w.t.

00:51:25.580 --> 00:51:28.580
Inshaallah tomorrow we will take a look

00:51:28.580 --> 00:51:30.580
At some of the narrations

00:51:30.580 --> 00:51:32.580
Where the prophet s.a.w

00:51:32.580 --> 00:51:36.580
Encouraged this newly formed nation

00:51:36.580 --> 00:51:38.580
Regarding character and conduct

00:51:38.580 --> 00:51:41.580
And what would actually build this nation

00:51:41.580 --> 00:51:43.580
And then what happened with Quraish

00:51:43.580 --> 00:51:46.580
Where they did not bear any patience

00:51:46.580 --> 00:51:47.580
They wanted to come

00:51:47.580 --> 00:51:50.580
And they really wanted to attack the mu'mineen

00:51:50.580 --> 00:51:52.580
And what happened as a result

00:51:52.580 --> 00:51:53.580
And the wars that took place

00:51:53.580 --> 00:51:57.580
May Allah s.w.t. grant us goodness and protection

00:51:57.580 --> 00:51:59.580
And may He make us from those who appreciate

00:51:59.580 --> 00:52:00.580
What had happened

00:52:00.580 --> 00:52:04.580
The sacrifice of those in order for it to get to us today

00:52:04.580 --> 00:52:05.580
Until we meet again

00:52:05.580 --> 00:52:08.580
May Allah s.w.t. bless our prophet Muhammed s.a.w

00:52:08.580 --> 00:52:09.580
Glory be to Allah

00:52:09.580 --> 00:52:10.580
Glory be to you

00:52:10.580 --> 00:52:12.580
We witness that there is no god but you

00:52:12.580 --> 00:52:13.580
We ask your forgiveness

00:52:13.580 --> 00:52:14.580
And we repent to you

00:52:14.580 --> 00:52:17.580
Praise be to Allah, the Lord of the worlds

00:52:17.580 --> 00:52:20.580
The Merciful, the Merciful

00:52:20.580 --> 00:52:23.580
Owner of the Day of Judgment

00:52:23.580 --> 00:52:25.580
It is You we worship
